#. [set_menu_item]: id=wmi_dehydration_helptxt
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/dehydration-utils.cfg:48
msgid "About Dehydration"
msgstr "Acerca de la deshidratación"

#. [event]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/dehydration-utils.cfg:65
msgid ""
"At the beginning of each daytime turn — Dawn, Morning, Midday, Afternoon, "
"and Dusk — all player-controlled living units, except bats, will suffer from "
"<b>thirst</b> unless they are standing on grassland or forested terrains; in "
"castles, encampments, or keeps; or hiding underground.\n"
"\n"
"Each turn spent thirsty reduces a unit’s attack damage by 1 and causes "
"$dehydration_loss hitpoints of damage. Thirsty units will regain full attack "
"strength at the start of each turn by refreshing at a village or water hex, "
"or being cared for by a healer. As with poison, a unit will not die of "
"thirst even if it is reduced to 1 hitpoint; likewise, its attack damage will "
"not drop below 1."
msgstr ""
"Al comienzo de cada turno diurno — Amanecer, Mañana, Mediodía, Tarde y "
"Anochecer — todas las unidades vivas controladas por el jugador, excepto los "
"murciélagos, sufrirán <b>sed</b> a menos que se encuentren en llanuras o "
"terrenos boscosos; en castillos, campamentos o fortalezas; o escondidas bajo "
"tierra.\n"
"\n"
"Cada turno sediento reduce el daño de ataque de la unidad en 1 y causa "
"$dehydration_loss puntos de daño. Las unidades sedientas recuperarán toda su "
"fuerza de ataque al inicio de cada turno al refrescarse en una aldea o en un "
"hexágono de agua, o si son atendidas por un sanador. Al igual que con el "
"veneno, una unidad no morirá de sed aunque sus puntos de vida se reduzcan a "
"1; del mismo modo, su daño de ataque no bajará de 1."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/dehydration-utils.cfg:166
msgid "Living units (except bats) are subject to dehydration in this scenario"
msgstr ""
"Las unidades vivas (excepto murciélagos) están sujetas a deshidratación en "
"este escenario"

#. [transient_message]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/first-time-help.cfg:14
msgid "UI^Character Description"
msgstr "Descripción de personaje"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/first-time-help.cfg:22
msgid ""
"<b>Galas</b> is an <b>Elvish Patrol Captain</b>. Despite his extensive "
"experience guarding the Valley, soon his journey will see him facing new and "
"unexpected threats. It is up to you to decide the exact path he shall take "
"to hone his skills."
msgstr ""

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/first-time-help.cfg:26
msgid ""
"<b>Anlindë</b> is an <b>Elvish Ascetic</b>. She has vast experience with "
"offensive magic, but she also has the ability to cure allied units of "
"poison. Keep in mind that she is the only unit of her kind."
msgstr ""
"<b>Anlindë</b> es una <b>Asceta élfica</b>. Tiene una gran experiencia en "
"magia ofensiva, pero también puede curar a las unidades aliadas del veneno. "
"Ten en cuenta que es la única unidad de su clase."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/first-time-help.cfg:30
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<b>Mal Keshar</b> is an <b>Archaic Lich</b>. Severely weakened by Anlindë’s "
"curse, it will take him a while to recover his full strength. Although he "
"may be a virtually unstoppable weapon against most living units, keep in "
"mind that he is weak against impact, arcane, and fire attacks — even more so "
"during daytime!"
msgstr ""
"<b>Mal Keshar</b> es un <b>Liche ancestral</b>. Aunque puede ser un arma "
"prácticamente imparable contra la mayoría de las unidades vivas, ten en "
"cuenta que es vulnerable a los ataques de impacto, arcanos y de fuego, "
"especialmente durante el día."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/first-time-help.cfg:34
msgid ""
"<b>Elynia</b> is the <b>Lady of Light</b>; she has great mobility, including "
"the ability to fly. Her skill with the staff as a melee weapon is also "
"remarkable, but never leave her alone when fighting well-armed opponents."
msgstr ""
"<b>Elynia</b> es la <b>Dama de la Luz</b>; posee gran movilidad, incluida la "
"capacidad de volar. Su habilidad con el bastón como arma cuerpo a cuerpo "
"también es notable, pero nunca la dejes sola cuando enfrente a oponentes "
"bien armados."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/first-time-help.cfg:38
msgid ""
"<b>Althurin</b> is one of the best <b>Dwarvish Runemasters</b> of Knalga. "
"His mastery of such craft allows him to accurately deal great damage with "
"his own hammer."
msgstr ""
"<b>Althurin</b> es uno de los mejores <b>Maestros de runas enanos</b> de "
"Knalga. Su maestría en el oficio le permite infligir un gran daño con su "
"propio martillo."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/first-time-help.cfg:42
msgid ""
"<b>Erathan</b> is an <b>Aragwaith Strongbow</b>. His skill with the bow is "
"not as great as that of elvish archers, but he aspires to either improve it "
"or enhance his ability with melee weapons such as the glaive. Nonetheless, "
"he is not used to fighting in open fields, so be careful when deciding where "
"he should attack from!"
msgstr ""
"<b>Erathan</b> es un <b>Arquero fuerte aragwaith</b>. Su habilidad con el "
"arco no es tan buena como la de los arqueros élficos, pero aspira a "
"mejorarla o a perfeccionar su destreza con armas cuerpo a cuerpo como la "
"guja. Aun así, no está acostumbrado a combatir en campo abierto, así que ten "
"cuidado al decidir desde dónde debe atacar."

#. [transient_message]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/first-time-help.cfg:112
msgid ""
"As a high-level unit under your control, Anlindë has special <b>After "
"Maximum Level Advancements (AMLAs)</b>. You can learn more about those by "
"right-clicking her and choosing the <b>Unit Advancements</b> option."
msgstr ""
"Como unidad de alto nivel bajo tu control, Anlindë tiene <b>Avances tras el "
"nivel máximo (AMLAs)</b> especiales. Puedes aprender más sobre ellos "
"haciendo clic derecho sobre ella y eligiendo la opción <b>Avances de unidad</"
"b>."

#. [transient_message]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/first-time-help.cfg:124
msgid ""
"As a high-level unit under your control, Elynia has special <b>After Maximum "
"Level Advancements (AMLAs)</b>. You can learn more about those by right-"
"clicking her and choosing the <b>Unit Advancements</b> option."
msgstr ""
"Como unidad de alto nivel bajo tu control, Elynia tiene <b>Avances tras el "
"nivel máximo (AMLAs)</b> especiales. Puedes aprender más sobre ellos "
"haciendo clic derecho sobre ella y eligiendo la opción <b>Avances de unidad</"
"b>."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:39
msgid "female^Hey! I just found $temp_gold_found pieces of gold in this chest!"
msgstr "¡Eh! ¡Acabo de encontrar $temp_gold_found piezas de oro en este cofre!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:40
msgid "Hey! I just found $temp_gold_found pieces of gold in this chest!"
msgstr "¡Eh! ¡Acabo de encontrar $temp_gold_found piezas de oro en este cofre!"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:61
msgid ""
"Holy water! I have read that our ancestors used to put it on their weapons "
"for fighting undead, as it is imbued with arcane energy, the greatest bane "
"of those unnatural creatures. Of course, it could be used against our people "
"as well — but it is fortunate that undead horrors are not capable of bearing "
"its power. That is probably why they hid it in this secret chamber."
msgstr ""
"¡Agua bendita! He leído que nuestros ancestros solían aplicarla a sus armas "
"para luchar contra los no muertos, ya que está impregnada de energía arcana, "
"la mayor perdición de esas criaturas antinaturales. Por supuesto, también "
"podría usarse contra nuestro pueblo, pero es afortunado que las horrorosas "
"criaturas no muertas no sean capaces de soportar su poder. Probablemente por "
"eso la escondieron en esta cámara secreta."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:62
msgid "I am not really suited for using this! Let someone else take it."
msgstr "¡No soy apto para usar esto! Que lo tome otra persona."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:88
msgid ""
"A gold ring, and there is an inscription on it. “You who take this ring will "
"be swifter and more graceful, no matter what weight you carry on your back.” "
"This would be useful here, since we are not very used to moving in these "
"rough, dark caves."
msgstr ""
"Un anillo de oro, y tiene una inscripción: “Tú que tomas este anillo, serás "
"más ágil y grácil, sin importar el peso que lleves a la espalda.” Esto sería "
"útil aquí, ya que no estamos muy acostumbrados a movernos en estas cuevas "
"oscuras y accidentadas."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:89
msgid "... But only a living creature could possibly make use of this ring."
msgstr "... Pero solo una criatura viva podría usar este anillo."

#. [object]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:96
msgid "Ring of Swiftness"
msgstr "Anillo de la agilidad"

#. [object]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:97
msgid ""
"This ring will grant the bearer swift movement, increasing maximum movement "
"by one unit per turn."
msgstr ""
"Este anillo otorgará al portador un movimiento ágil, aumentando su "
"movimiento máximo en una unidad por turno."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:120
msgid ""
"This is the famed artifact we dug up from the sorcerer’s tomb. It feels "
"sacrilegious to pick it up — not only because of the fact we are desecrating "
"someone’s final resting place, but also because the staff seems imbued with "
"an unnatural energy, clearly a product of forbidden sorcery. Then again, our "
"‘venerable’ leadership somehow sees it fit to employ <i>necromancy</i> in "
"our quest across the desert... so, who am I to decide on these matters?"
msgstr ""
"Este es el famoso artefacto que desenterramos de la tumba del hechicero. Se "
"siente sacrílego tomarlo, no solo porque estamos profanando el lugar de "
"descanso final de alguien, sino también porque el bastón parece impregnado "
"de una energía antinatural, claramente producto de una hechicería prohibida. "
"Sin embargo, nuestra «venerable» dirigencia de alguna manera considera "
"apropiado emplear <i>nigromancia</i> en nuestra travesía por el desierto... "
"así que, ¿quién soy yo para decidir sobre estos asuntos?"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:121
msgid "This is probably best used by one of our more experienced magic users."
msgstr ""
"Probablemente sea mejor que lo use uno de nuestros usuarios de magia más "
"experimentados."

#. [then]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:128
msgid "touch of petrichor"
msgstr "toque de petricor"

#. [else]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:131
msgid "staff of petrichor"
msgstr "bastón de petricor"

#. [object]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:140
msgid "Staff of Petrichor"
msgstr "Bastón de Petricor"

#. [object]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:141
msgid ""
"During offense, the lingering dark energies within this staff allow the "
"bearer to petrify a single lower-level enemy for the duration of a single "
"turn. Additionally, the target is temporarily afflicted with the <b>mark</b> "
"status effect upon turning back to normal."
msgstr ""
"Durante el ataque, las energías oscuras persistentes en este bastón permiten "
"al portador petrificar a un solo enemigo de nivel inferior durante un turno "
"completo. Además, el objetivo queda temporalmente afectado por el estado "
"<b>marcado</b> al volver a la normalidad."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:164
msgid ""
"My body feels heavy holding this staff in my hand, as if an invisible force "
"was constantly pulling me to the ground. I pray to the Lords of Light that "
"it is only a temporary affliction..."
msgstr ""
"Mi cuerpo se siente pesado al sostener este bastón en la mano, como si una "
"fuerza invisible me estuviera jalando constantemente hacia el suelo. Rezo a "
"los Señores de la Luz para que sea solo una aflicción temporal..."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:172
msgid ""
"An enchanted bow! I have read that ancient armies used to hire powerful "
"warlocks to grant mundane weapons special powers such as poisoning without "
"need of preparing them beforehand, which is the main lack of those dumb "
"orcish slayers. Well, this one seems to have such a power, judging by the "
"fine inscription on it."
msgstr ""
"¡Un arco encantado! He leído que los ejércitos antiguos solían contratar "
"poderosos brujos para dotar a las armas comunes de poderes especiales, como "
"envenenar sin necesidad de prepararlas de antemano, que es la principal "
"carencia de esos torpes asesinos orcos. Bueno, este parece tener ese poder, "
"a juzgar por la fina inscripción que lleva."

#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:173
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/05b_Cursed_Plateau.cfg:939
msgid "I am not suited to use this weapon! Let someone else pick it up."
msgstr "¡No estoy capacitado para usar esta arma! Que la tome otra persona."

#. [object]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:180
msgid "Poisonous Bow"
msgstr "Arco venenoso"

#. [object]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:181
msgid ""
"This bow has been enchanted. Every arrow shot with it will poison its target."
msgstr ""
"Este arco ha sido encantado. Cada flecha disparada con él envenenará a su "
"objetivo."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:189
msgid ""
"The unit picks up the ordinary-looking bow, and immediately feels a chilling "
"energy flow to their body. Out of curiosity, they decide to shoot a nearby "
"wandering rat with it. The hapless creature begins emanating a disgusting "
"smell like a concentrated mix of urine and decomposing flesh as it convulses "
"and promptly dies."
msgstr ""
"La unidad toma el arco de aspecto ordinario y de inmediato siente una "
"energía helada fluir por su cuerpo. Por curiosidad, decide dispararle a una "
"rata que deambulaba cerca. La desdichada criatura comienza a emitir un olor "
"asqueroso, como una mezcla concentrada de orina y carne en descomposición, "
"mientras se convulsiona y muere al instante."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:194
msgid ""
"We have never allowed the use of poison out of compassion towards the "
"living, but our enemies do not seem to particularly care about such things "
"themselves."
msgstr ""
"Nunca hemos permitido el uso de veneno por compasión hacia los vivos, pero "
"nuestros enemigos no parecen preocuparse mucho por esas cosas."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:199
msgid ""
"(<i>cackles</i>) Good, good. You have become quite the competent war leader, "
"boy. Do not let such petty things as old-fashioned war customs discourage "
"you from broadening your horizons."
msgstr ""
"(<i>carcajea</i>) Bien, bien. Te has convertido en un líder de guerra "
"bastante competente, muchacho. No dejes que cosas tan insignificantes como "
"las anticuadas costumbres de guerra te desanimen a ampliar tus horizontes."

#. [effect]: type=pierce
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:205
msgid "poisonous bow"
msgstr "arco venenoso"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:243
msgid ""
"How could this beautiful armor be abandoned in these deep caves? I suppose "
"someone dropped it during an evacuation or such, since it looks like it "
"hasn’t been worn before — well preserved nevertheless. It would fit an "
"elvish or undead warrior of ours fine. We are rather short on battle gear "
"and I don’t think its original owner would mind if we borrow and use it."
msgstr ""
"¿Cómo pudo esta hermosa armadura ser abandonada en estas profundas cavernas? "
"Supongo que alguien la dejó caer durante una evacuación o algo así, ya que "
"parece no haber sido usada antes — aunque está bien conservada. Le vendría "
"bien a un guerrero élfico o no-muerto de los nuestros. Nos falta equipo de "
"batalla, y no creo que a su dueño original le importe si la tomamos prestada "
"y la usamos."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:244
msgid "Only a trained warrior may don this armor!"
msgstr "¡Solo un guerrero entrenado puede vestir esta armadura!"

#. [object]: id={ID}
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:250
msgid "Void Armor"
msgstr "Armadura del Vacío"

#. [object]: id={ID}
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:252
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A beautiful chest plate crafted from shimmering black steel. The unit "
"wearing this armor gains +15% resistance to blade and pierce damage, +20% to "
"impact damage, and +10% to fire damage."
msgstr ""
"Una hermosa coraza forjada con acero negro brillante, ¡la Armadura del Vacío "
"es prácticamente impenetrable para las armas físicas!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:271
msgid ""
"You struggle to lift and don the heavy plate. Once worn, however, it is "
"amazingly comfortable. You have increased resistance to all physical damage!"
msgstr ""
"Te cuesta levantar y ponerte la pesada coraza. Sin embargo, una vez puesta "
"resulta sorprendentemente cómoda. ¡Tu resistencia a todo daño físico ha "
"aumentado!"

#. [value]: id=void_armor
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:287
msgid "void armor"
msgstr "armadura del vacío"

#. [value]: id=void_armor
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:288
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Void Armor grants the following resistances:\n"
"\n"
"Blade:  +15%\n"
"Pierce: +15%\n"
"Impact: +20%\n"
"Fire:   +10%"
msgstr ""
"La Armadura del Vacío concede las siguientes resistencias:\n"
"\n"
"Corte:   50%\n"
"Penetración:  50%\n"
"Impacto:  60%\n"
"Fuego:   +10%"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:315
msgid ""
"The arrows in this barrel are some of the most expensive weaponry ever "
"devised by the dwarves of Herthgar, although most of the credit for the "
"design goes to their fallen kin in Gnalvarden. Each arrow shaft has tiny "
"runes engraved on them that react upon entering a living target and ignite "
"the explosive tip. The resulting explosion deals great damage not just to "
"the arrow’s target, but also to anything directly behind it. Surely this "
"will come in handy later on, but we should make sure to hand these only to a "
"very skilled archer so as to avoid wasting them — besides, it would not do "
"for a novice to accidentally blow up one of our own."
msgstr ""
"Las flechas de este barril son de las armas más caras que jamás idearon los "
"enanos de Herthgar, aunque la mayor parte del mérito del diseño corresponde "
"a sus parientes caídos en Gnalvarden. Cada asta de flecha tiene diminutas "
"runas grabadas que reaccionan al penetrar un objetivo vivo e incendian la "
"punta explosiva. La explosión resultante causa gran daño no solo al "
"objetivo, sino también a todo lo que se encuentre directamente detrás de él. "
"Sin duda esto será útil más adelante, pero debemos asegurarnos de "
"entregarlas solo a un arquero muy hábil para evitar desperdiciarlas; además, "
"no sería apropiado que un novato hiciera estallar accidentalmente a uno de "
"los nuestros."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:316
msgid ""
"These arrows are more befitting for a skilled archer, which I certainly am "
"not."
msgstr ""
"Estas flechas son más adecuadas para un arquero experimentado, lo cual "
"ciertamente no soy."

#. [object]: id=explosive_rune_arrows
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:322
msgid "Explosive Runic Arrows"
msgstr "Flechas rúnicas explosivas"

#. [object]: id=explosive_rune_arrows
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:324
msgid ""
"When used against a living target, these arrows will explode dealing 80% "
"damage to the unit directly behind it, regardless of its allegiance or type."
msgstr ""
"Cuando se usan contra un objetivo vivo, estas flechas explotarán causando un "
"80% de daño a la unidad que se encuentre directamente detrás, sin importar "
"su lealtad o tipo."

#. [effect]: type=fire
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:332
msgid "explosive arrows (6)"
msgstr "flechas explosivas (6)"

#. [literal]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:409
msgid "explosive arrows"
msgstr "flechas explosivas"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:432
msgid ""
"Careful! It would hurt me to lose one of our men by accidentally triggering "
"an explosive artifact like those."
msgstr ""
"¡Cuidado! Me dolería perder a uno de nuestros hombres por activar "
"accidentalmente un artefacto explosivo como esos."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:437
msgid "(<i>gulp</i>) I will make sure to handle them with care, sir."
msgstr "(<i>traga saliva</i>) Me aseguraré de manejarlas con cuidado, señor."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:443
msgid ""
"Heh. I don’t even need to worry about them accidentally exploding in my "
"quiver!"
msgstr ""
"Heh. ¡Ni siquiera necesito preocuparme de que exploten accidentalmente en mi "
"carcaj!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:448
msgid "He he, yes, indeed. Is it not great?"
msgstr "Je je, sí, efectivamente. ¿No es genial?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:453
msgid "Just make sure to aim those at our enemies, Mal Keshar."
msgstr "Asegúrate de apuntar esas flechas a nuestros enemigos, Mal Keshar."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:458
msgid "Pah, distrustful much?"
msgstr "Pah, ¿desconfiada acaso?"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:468
msgid ""
"As I lift this enchanted bow, my vision appears to become sharper! This will "
"surely prove useful later."
msgstr ""
"¡Al levantar este arco encantado, mi visión parece agudizarse! Sin duda "
"resultará útil más adelante."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:469
msgid "Only a strong and experienced archer could possibly draw this bow!"
msgstr "¡Solo un arquero fuerte y experimentado podría tensar este arco!"

#. [object]: id=accuracy_bow
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:475
msgid "Enchanted Longbow of Visual Acuity"
msgstr "Arco largo encantado de agudeza visual"

#. [object]: id=accuracy_bow
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:477
msgid ""
"The unit’s ranged attacks are permanently given the Marksman weapon special."
msgstr ""
"Los ataques a distancia de la unidad reciben permanentemente la habilidad de "
"arma Tirador."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:497
msgid ""
"I feel a chilly aura around this sword. I wonder if... All right, woah, even "
"the hilt is extremely cold to the touch! The blade freezes everything it "
"touches, so this might come in handy when fighting one of the larger demons, "
"perhaps. Still, I suspect only someone strong enough to withstand the cold "
"should wield this weapon."
msgstr ""
"Siento un aura helada alrededor de esta espada. Me pregunto si... ¡Vaya, "
"incluso la empuñadura está extremadamente fría al tacto! La hoja congela "
"todo lo que toca, así que podría ser útil para luchar contra alguno de los "
"demonios más grandes, tal vez. Aun así, sospecho que solo alguien lo "
"suficientemente fuerte para soportar el frío debería empuñar esta arma."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:498
msgid "Only a living sword user can wield this sword!"
msgstr "¡Solo un espadachín viviente puede empuñar esta espada!"

#. [object]: id=chilling_blade
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:504
msgid "Glacial Gladius"
msgstr "Gladio glacial"

#. [object]: id=chilling_blade
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:506
msgid ""
"While wielding this sword, the unit’s melee attack damage is increased by +1 "
"and deals cold damage. Additionally, the unit’s maximum hitpoints are "
"decreased by 5%."
msgstr ""
"Al empuñar esta espada, el daño de ataque cuerpo a cuerpo de la unidad "
"aumenta en +1 y pasa a infligir daño por frío. Además, los puntos de vida "
"máximos de la unidad se reducen en un 5%."

#. [effect]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:514
msgid "glacial gladius"
msgstr "gladio glacial"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:540
msgid ""
"The scroll next to this amulet says: “This artifact imbues projectiles shot "
"by the bearer with strong arcane energy, casting fear upon their unholy "
"enemies.” I imagine the demons stole this from somewhere and did not find "
"actual use for it."
msgstr ""
"El pergamino junto a este amuleto dice: «Este artefacto imbuye los "
"proyectiles lanzados por su portador con una poderosa energía arcana, "
"infundiendo temor en sus impíos enemigos.» Me imagino que los demonios lo "
"robaron de algún lugar y no le encontraron un uso real."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:541
msgid "Only mundane creatures can use this amulet."
msgstr "Solo las criaturas mundanas pueden usar este amuleto."

#. [object]: id=arcane_shot_amulet
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:545
msgid "Amulet of the Divine Breeze"
msgstr "Amuleto de la Brisa Divina"

#. [object]: id=arcane_shot_amulet
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:548
msgid ""
"This amulet will grant the bearer arcane power to their ranged attacks, and "
"increases their resistance to arcane damage by 10%."
msgstr ""
"Este amuleto otorgará al portador poder arcano en sus ataques a distancia y "
"aumentará su resistencia al daño arcano en un 10%."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:577
msgid ""
"It is a strength potion. The flask contains only enough for one person, but "
"surely it will come in handy when we finally confront that Chaos Emperor. "
"Who should take it?"
msgstr ""
"Es una poción de fuerza. El frasco contiene suficiente solo para una "
"persona, pero sin duda será útil cuando finalmente nos enfrentemos a ese "
"Emperador del Caos. ¿Quién debería tomarla?"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:578
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:617
msgid "This potion can only be used by living beings. Let another take it."
msgstr "Esta poción solo puede ser usada por seres vivos. Que la tome otro."

#. [object]: id=s21_strength_potion
#. [object]: id=e1l7_strength_potion
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:586
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/07_Goliath.cfg:613
msgid "Potion of Strength"
msgstr "Poción de la fuerza"

#. [object]: id=s21_strength_potion
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:589
msgid ""
"The drinker’s strength is increased, adding 1 damage point to their melee "
"attacks, and adding 8 points to their total HP."
msgstr ""
"La fuerza de quien la beba se incrementa, añadiendo 1 punto de daño a sus "
"ataques cuerpo a cuerpo y 8 puntos a su vida total."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:616
msgid ""
"This potion is supposed to make one more agile. I wonder if this is what "
"makes those demons so hard to hit rather than natural skill."
msgstr ""
"Se supone que esta poción vuelve a uno más ágil. Me pregunto si esto es lo "
"que hace que esos demonios sean tan difíciles de alcanzar, más que una "
"habilidad natural."

#. [object]: id=s21_deftness_potion
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:625
msgid "Potion of Deftness"
msgstr "Poción de la agilidad"

#. [object]: id=s21_deftness_potion
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/items.cfg:628
msgid ""
"This magic potion will increase the drinker’s movement points by one, and "
"increase the inflicted base damage of its ranged attacks by one, if "
"applicable."
msgstr ""
"Esta poción mágica aumentará en uno los puntos de movimiento de quien la "
"beba y también incrementará en uno el daño base de sus ataques a distancia, "
"si los tiene."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/objective-utils.cfg:4
msgid "New objectives:"
msgstr "Nuevos objetivos:"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/objective-utils.cfg:7
msgid "Current objectives:"
msgstr "Objetivos actuales:"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/objective-utils.cfg:10
msgid "Initial objectives:"
msgstr "Objetivos iniciales:"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/objective-utils.cfg:13
msgid "Final objectives:"
msgstr "Objetivos finales:"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:58
msgid ""
"Rise, fallen warrior! Rise once more and slay the foe who felled you in your "
"hour of glory!"
msgstr ""
"¡Levántate, guerrero caído! ¡Levántate una vez más y mata al enemigo que te "
"derribó en tu hora de gloria!"

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:163
msgid "You failed to protect me. Aargh..."
msgstr "Fallaste en protegerme. Aargh..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:199
msgid "Ah, excellent, a fresh recruit!"
msgstr "¡Ah, excelente, un recluta fresco!"

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:208
msgid "Alas. It’s been my best time with you, friends..."
msgstr "Ay... Han sido mis mejores momentos con ustedes, amigos..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:213
msgid "He, he, he..."
msgstr "Je, je, je..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:218
msgid "(<i>glaring</i>) Don’t do it."
msgstr "(<i>mirando fijamente</i>) No lo hagas."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:223
msgid "Um... all right. May I ask <i>why</i>?"
msgstr "Eh... de acuerdo. ¿Puedo preguntar <i>por qué</i>?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:228
msgid ""
"He was very helpful with us — more than I ever expected from anyone of his "
"kind. It would be very unseemly for us to disturb his well-deserved rest."
msgstr ""
"Fue muy servicial con nosotros, más de lo que jamás habría esperado de "
"alguien de su clase. Sería muy impropio de nosotros perturbar su merecido "
"descanso."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:233
msgid "As you wish, lady. Hmph."
msgstr "Como desees, mi señora. Hmph."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:242
msgid "Alas. I wish I could’ve seen the end with you..."
msgstr "Ay... Ojalá hubiera podido ver el final con ustedes..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:251
msgid ""
"Vanquished by these foul enemies... it should not have ended like this..."
msgstr "Derrotado por estos asquerosos enemigos... no debería terminar así..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:260
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/23B_Until_Death.cfg:1421
msgid "Oh, the sweet, cold embrace of death... it has been far too long..."
msgstr ""
"Ah, el dulce y frío abrazo de la muerte... ha pasado demasiado tiempo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Erathan
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:269
msgid "I am finished..."
msgstr "Estoy acabado..."

#. [message]: speaker=Erathan
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:278
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/23B_Until_Death.cfg:1403
msgid "So this is the end of the road for me..."
msgstr "Así que este es el fin del camino para mí..."

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:287
msgid "The darkness... it is taking me away..."
msgstr "La oscuridad... me está arrastrando..."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:292
msgid "No! Elynia!"
msgstr "¡No! ¡Elynia!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:301
msgid ""
"I’m sorry Galas... Hopefully you will be able to finish our journey without "
"me..."
msgstr "Lo siento, Galas... Espero que puedas terminar nuestro viaje sin mí..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:310
msgid "I suppose I should have seen this coming..."
msgstr "Supongo que debí haberlo visto venir..."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:319
msgid "I have much... left... to do—"
msgstr "Tengo mucho... por hacer aún—"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:328
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/23B_Until_Death.cfg:1375
msgid "Why... did it have to end like this..."
msgstr "¿Por qué...tuvo que terminar así...?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lédinor
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:337
msgid "It is the end for me. At last I shall rest..."
msgstr "Es mi final. Por fin podré descansar..."

#. [message]: speaker=Althurin
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:346
msgid "Well, at least I tried... Ugh—"
msgstr "Bueno, al menos lo intenté... Ugh—"

#. [message]: speaker=King Asthorgar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:355
msgid "Argh! This is the end for me."
msgstr "¡Argh! Este es mi fin."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:360
msgid "We were supposed to protect the king of Herthgar!"
msgstr "¡Se suponía que debíamos proteger al rey de Herthgar!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:378
msgid "The Ring of the Revenant glows in the nick of time..."
msgstr "El Anillo del Revenant brilla en el último momento..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:396
msgid "A powerful force... it is pulling my soul... argh..."
msgstr "Una fuerza poderosa... está arrastrando mi alma... argh..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:401
msgid "Um... this doesn’t seem good. Noooot good at all."
msgstr "Eh... esto no parece bueno. Para nada bueno."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:406
msgid "AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH—"
msgstr "AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH—"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:470
msgid "Wha— what happened?"
msgstr "¿Q-qué pasó?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:475
msgid "The ring brought her back to life...?"
msgstr "¿El anillo la devolvió a la vida...?"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:480
msgid ""
"I suppose that’s one possible way to look at it. Faerie spirits are "
"perpetually stuck in an intermediate state between life and death, between "
"the material and spirit realms. The ring that once belonged to the second "
"Wesnothian Emperor fully pulled her back into ours... or wherever we are, "
"actually."
msgstr ""
"Supongo que es una forma posible de verlo. Los espíritus feéricos están "
"atrapados perpetuamente en un estado intermedio entre la vida y la muerte, "
"entre los reinos material y espiritual. El anillo que alguna vez perteneció "
"al segundo Emperador de Wesnoth la trajo completamente de vuelta al "
"nuestro... o a donde sea que estemos, en realidad."

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:496
msgid "She’s so pretty!"
msgstr "¡Es tan bonita!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. He's saying she will be killed and used as raw material for wood-related
#. commercial activities, of course.
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:503
msgid ""
"I would not mess with a half-faerie half-tree creature if I were you. Only "
"heartbreak lies that way. Plus she will probably inspire someone to pursue a "
"career in furniture design before we are done with our little adventure — if "
"you know what I mean."
msgstr ""
"Yo no me metería con una criatura medio feérica, medio árbol, si fuera tú. "
"Solo encontrarás desdicha por ese camino. Además, probablemente inspire a "
"alguien a dedicarse al diseño de muebles antes de que terminemos esta "
"pequeña aventura, si sabes a lo que me refiero."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:524
msgid "Neep, neep? Neep!"
msgstr "¡Nip, nip! ¿Nip!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:529
msgid "Yes! Ha, ha, ha, yes!"
msgstr "¡Sí! ¡Ja, ja, ja, sí!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-deaths.cfg:534
msgid ""
"... Sigh. I can only imagine how excited Irylean will be when she hears of "
"this."
msgstr ""
"... Suspiro. Solo puedo imaginar lo emocionada que estará Irylean cuando se "
"entere de esto."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/scenario-utils.cfg:41
msgid "male^Mysterious Voice"
msgstr "voz misteriosa"

#. [time]: id=v_underground
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/schedules.cfg:10
msgid "Volcanic Underground"
msgstr "Subterráneo volcánico"

#. [time]: id=illuminated_underground
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/schedules.cfg:38
msgid "Illuminated Underground"
msgstr "Subterráneo iluminado"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/special-notes.cfg:6
msgid ""
"When this unit’s dreadful attack is used on offensive, it decreases the "
"damage the unit may take in retaliation, but only if the victim is of equal "
"or lesser level."
msgstr ""
"Cuando esta unidad usa su temible ataque en ofensiva, reduce el daño que "
"puede recibir en represalia, pero solo si la víctima es de nivel igual o "
"inferior."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/special-notes.cfg:9
msgid ""
"This unit’s presence intimidates adjacent level 0-1 enemy units, causing "
"them to deal less damage and be unable to maintain their zone of control."
msgstr ""
"La presencia de esta unidad intimida a las unidades enemigas adyacentes de "
"nivel 0-1, lo que provoca que inflijan menos daño y no puedan mantener su "
"zona de control."

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/special-notes.cfg:12
msgid ""
"This unit can either remove poison from itself or regenerate 4 hitpoints "
"each turn."
msgstr ""
"Esta unidad puede eliminar su veneno o regenerar 4 puntos de vida cada turno."

#. [checkbox]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:13
msgid ""
"Select this option if you wish to see brief descriptions of characters and "
"their gameplay when they are selected on the map for the first time."
msgstr ""
"Selecciona esta opción si deseas ver breves descripciones de los personajes "
"y su forma de jugar la primera vez que los selecciones en el mapa."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:30
msgid "From the personal journal of Lord Galas of the Forest Elves."
msgstr "Del diario personal del Señor Galas de los Elfos del Bosque."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:33
msgid ""
"“Our ancestors settled this land ages ago, seeking shelter from the hostile "
"outside world. They hailed from forests which have long withered away; the "
"endless expanse of sand could not possibly offer our kind much more than "
"vicious enemies and a slow, agonizing death. It is said that thousands of "
"elves fell before the survivors finally came across this green valley. As if "
"by the grace of the Lords of Light themselves, it emerged from the ruins of "
"a once green and lush world in our moment of dire need.\n"
"\n"
"Defending our valley from intruders has never been an easy task. A small "
"portion of our troops are trained in the ways of navigating and fighting in "
"the sands from a young age and assigned to patrol groups in charge of "
"warding our frontiers. It is not a particularly rewarding mission, but it "
"has allowed us to prosper as a united people."
msgstr ""
"“Nuestros ancestros se asentaron en estas tierras hace eras, buscando "
"refugio del hostil mundo exterior. Provenían de bosques que hace mucho "
"tiempo se marchitaron; la interminable extensión de arena no podía ofrecer a "
"los nuestros mucho más que enemigos despiadados y una lenta y agonizante "
"muerte. Se dice que miles de elfos cayeron antes de que los supervivientes "
"finalmente encontrasen este valle verde. Como si fuese por la gracia de los "
"propios Señores de la Luz, emergió de las ruinas de un mundo que alguna vez "
"fue verde y exuberante, en nuestro momento de extrema necesidad.\n"
"\n"
"Defender nuestro valle de los intrusos nunca ha sido una tarea fácil. Una "
"pequeña porción de nuestras tropas está entrenada desde joven en las formas "
"de navegar y luchar en las arenas, y se les asigna a grupos de patrulla "
"encargados de vigilar nuestras fronteras. No es una misión particularmente "
"gratificante, pero nos ha permitido prosperar como un pueblo unido."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:38
msgid ""
"My father was on duty leading his group one night, against a band of nomadic "
"humans. Barbarians unwilling to converse with speaking creatures not born of "
"their kin’s blood, and only intent on conquering and taking what they "
"believed theirs by right.\n"
"\n"
"A sling bullet broke his skull as he defended an injured comrade."
msgstr ""
"Mi padre estaba de guardia liderando su grupo una noche, contra una banda de "
"humanos nómadas. Barbaros que se negaban a conversar con criaturas parlantes "
"que no compartían la sangre de su linaje, y sólo tenían la intención de "
"conquistar y tomar lo que creían suyo por derecho.\n"
"\n"
"Una piedra de honda le rompió el cráneo mientras defendía a un camarada "
"herido."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:43
msgid ""
"At the time I was shocked by his death — a graceless end to a valiant life. "
"I cried for the last time at his funeral. On memory of him I swore to become "
"the best, advancing beyond the ranks of my comrades until I was one of the "
"best fighters and commanders amongst my people, despite my age.\n"
"\n"
"Anlindë has taken care of me like her own son since then. She has been to me "
"the mother I never had, often spending far too much time caring for me "
"rather than her own duties with the wounded and infirm."
msgstr ""
"En ese momento quedé conmocionado por su muerte — un final sin gracia para "
"una vida valiente. Lloré por última vez en su funeral. En su memoria juré "
"convertirme en el mejor, ascendiendo más allá de las filas de mis camaradas "
"hasta ser uno de los mejores luchadores y comandantes de mi pueblo, a pesar "
"de mi edad.\n"
"\n"
"Anlindë me ha cuidado como a su propio hijo desde entonces. Ha sido para mí "
"la madre que nunca tuve, dedicando a menudo demasiado tiempo a cuidarme en "
"lugar de a sus propios deberes con los heridos y enfermos."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:48
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/01_Border_Patrol.cfg:4
msgid "Border Patrol"
msgstr "Patrulla fronteriza"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:50
msgid ""
"Recently, the frequency and intensity of the hostile incursions has "
"increased. We can detect no single hand behind them, but it is as if they "
"were thrust into our domains by some force greater than their own petty "
"greed and rage. They throw themselves onto our blades and arrows as if death "
"were a better alternative than retreat. Our patrol groups are growing in "
"size to resist, but the pace of recruiting is becoming harder to maintain. "
"Most people do not crave the chance to risk their lives in combat against "
"such determined foes.\n"
"\n"
"Then one day, we discovered the source of the outsiders’ frenzy."
msgstr ""
"Últimamente, la frecuencia e intensidad de las incursiones hostiles ha "
"aumentado. No podemos detectar una mano única detrás de ellas, pero es como "
"si fueran empujados a nuestros dominios por alguna fuerza mayor que su "
"propia mezquina codicia y furia. Se lanzan contra nuestras espadas y flechas "
"como si la muerte fuese una mejor alternativa que la retirada. Nuestros "
"grupos de patrulla están creciendo en tamaño para resistir, pero el ritmo de "
"reclutamiento se vuelve cada vez más difícil de mantener. La mayoría de la "
"gente no ansía la oportunidad de arriesgar sus vidas en combate contra "
"enemigos tan decididos.\n"
"\n"
"Entonces, un día descubrimos la fuente de la locura de los forasteros."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:60
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/02_A_Real_Confrontation.cfg:4
msgid "A Real Confrontation"
msgstr "Una confrontación real"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:62
msgid ""
"It was quite a success, but the fighting technique of those humans was more "
"professional, coordinated, and accurate than those of the regular nomadic "
"skirmishers. That worried me initially, and I would have organized a "
"scouting party into the desert if we had been in any condition to do so.\n"
"\n"
"Our group was greatly weakened by the battle, so we withdrew back to the "
"main keep in the valley. Another patrol group took our place and was "
"scheduled to return in three days. That was not to happen. Instead, enemies "
"came to us with our kin’s skulls mounted atop their banner-poles. Driving "
"them forth would not be easy."
msgstr ""
"Fue un éxito considerable, pero la técnica de combate de esos humanos era "
"más profesional, coordinada y precisa que la de los habituales hostigadores "
"nómadas. Eso me preocupó al principio, y habría organizado un grupo de "
"exploración en el desierto si hubiéramos estado en condiciones de hacerlo.\n"
"\n"
"Nuestro grupo quedó muy debilitado por la batalla, así que nos retiramos al "
"torreón principal en el valle. Otro grupo de patrulla tomó nuestro lugar y "
"debía regresar en tres días. Eso no ocurrió. En su lugar, los enemigos "
"llegaron con los cráneos de nuestros hermanos montados en lo alto de sus "
"estandartes. Expulsarlos no sería fácil."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:73
msgid ""
"We were shocked when we tallied our numbers. Barely a thousand of us "
"survived the battle in the valley. Most of the dead likely perished in the "
"villages burnt by our foes, helpless and frightened. Alas, they met one of "
"the most painful deaths one could ever imagine.\n"
"\n"
"When I thought about what forced us from our ancient home, the one place we "
"had lived in safety on this war-torn and barren world, I felt my stomach "
"clench in terror. Anlindë was a wise sorceress, but I regretted not being "
"strong enough to ignore her counsel. I could not help but think that had we "
"stayed, we could have fought back and somehow emerged victorious."
msgstr ""
"Nos quedamos impactados al contar nuestras fuerzas. Apenas un millar de "
"nosotros sobrevivió a la batalla en el valle. La mayoría de los muertos "
"probablemente pereció en las aldeas incendiadas por nuestros enemigos, "
"indefensos y asustados. Por desgracia, sufrieron una de las muertes más "
"dolorosas que uno pueda imaginar.\n"
"\n"
"Cuando pensaba en lo que nos obligó a abandonar nuestro antiguo hogar, el "
"único lugar donde habíamos vivido a salvo en este mundo arrasado por la "
"guerra y yermo, sentí el estómago encogerse de terror. Anlindë era una sabia "
"hechicera, pero lamenté no haber sido lo bastante fuerte como para ignorar "
"su consejo. No podía evitar pensar que si nos hubiésemos quedado, podríamos "
"haber luchado y de algún modo salir victoriosos."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:78
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:4
msgid "Memories from the Depths"
msgstr "Memorias de las Profundidades"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:79
msgid ""
"I but hoped that fleeing into the depths was a wise decision, and that "
"Lédinor’s efforts were not wasted."
msgstr ""
"Sólo esperaba que huir hacia las profundidades hubiese sido una decisión "
"sabia, y que los esfuerzos de Lédinor no se hubiesen desperdiciado."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:88
msgid ""
"Northwest. That was the direction we had to go, if Mal Keshar’s words were "
"to be believed. We were to seek our saviors in the depths of the largest "
"mountain range within our reach; a place formerly inhabited by the artisans "
"of the earth, the dwarves of Knalga.\n"
"\n"
"According to Anlindë, he was a tormented soul. A man who began his journey "
"fighting for what he believed to be a noble cause before veering off the "
"road into an eternal abyss that tainted and twisted and destroyed him. Now "
"that man’s shadow walked alongside us under the surface of Irdya. I fear "
"what future generations will think of us who allowed such a monster on our "
"side... if we survive long enough to leave any descendants, that is.\n"
"\n"
"In spite of his evident bitterness, the necromancer did not make a second "
"attempt against us. I wondered if this was a ruse or he was just daunted by "
"Anlindë’s close watch."
msgstr ""
"Noroeste. Esa era la dirección en la que debíamos ir, si las palabras de Mal "
"Keshar eran dignas de confianza. Debíamos buscar a nuestros salvadores en "
"las profundidades de la cordillera más grande a nuestro alcance; un lugar "
"anteriormente habitado por los artesanos de la tierra, los enanos de "
"Knalga.\n"
"\n"
"Según Anlindë, él era un alma atormentada. Un hombre que comenzó su camino "
"luchando por lo que creía una causa noble, antes de desviarse hacia un "
"abismo eterno que lo corrompió, retorció y destruyó. Ahora la sombra de ese "
"hombre caminaba junto a nosotros bajo la superficie de Irdya. Temo lo que "
"las generaciones futuras pensarán de nosotros por permitir que tal monstruo "
"estuviese de nuestro lado... si es que sobrevivimos el tiempo suficiente "
"para dejar algún descendiente.\n"
"\n"
"A pesar de su evidente amargura, el nigromante no hizo un segundo intento "
"contra nosotros. Me preguntaba si esto era un engaño o si simplemente estaba "
"intimidado por la atenta vigilancia de Anlindë."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:95
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/04_Over_the_Sands.cfg:4
msgid "Over the Sands"
msgstr "Sobre las arenas"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:96
msgid ""
"My uneasiness throughout the journey underground was not solely due to the "
"dark sorcerer’s presence, though.\n"
"\n"
"Anlindë shunned my questions about the ‘catastrophe’ mentioned by her and "
"Mal Keshar during their initial conversation. It was no surprise to me that "
"the lich would refuse to answer my questions, but why would Anlindë shun my "
"curiosity as well? Is the order of sorcerers she belongs to not dedicated to "
"preserving and communicating our lore to any elf who would display an "
"interest in it? And how could she, with her words alone, weaken such a "
"peculiar adversary where other sorcerers would fail?"
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, mi inquietud durante el viaje subterráneo no se debía "
"únicamente a la presencia del hechicero oscuro.\n"
"\n"
"Anlindë evitaba mis preguntas sobre la ‘catástrofe’ que mencionaron ella y "
"Mal Keshar durante su conversación inicial. No me sorprendió que el liche "
"rehusara responder a mis preguntas, pero ¿por qué Anlindë también esquivaba "
"mi curiosidad? ¿Acaso la orden de hechiceros a la que ella pertenece no está "
"dedicada a preservar y comunicar nuestro saber a cualquier elfo que muestre "
"interés? ¿Y cómo pudo ella, sólo con sus palabras, debilitar a un adversario "
"tan peculiar donde otros hechiceros fracasarían?"

#. [part]
#. NOTE: The second paragraph in this block is reused for scenario 5b's
#. story text below.
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:110
msgid ""
"We left Lady Unarye in charge of the Eisenstone clan’s lands for a few "
"weeks, allowing our civilians to advance over the sands relatively "
"unhindered as we continued to clear the path ahead. We tried to make up for "
"the clan’s losses as best as we could, trading knowledge, weapons, and "
"valuables with the locals. Their distrust and hatred slowly gave way to a "
"more peaceful cultural exchange — an advantageous outcome for both parties.\n"
"\n"
"The long desert march drew the attention of many more desert dwellers in the "
"region, most of them fearful of our numbers, weapons, allies... and our "
"species. However, once curiosity overcame their initial fear, some of them "
"approached us with no ill intentions. Mal Keshar saw it fitting to take "
"advantage of this situation."
msgstr ""
"Dejamos a Lady Unarye a cargo de las tierras del clan Eisenstone durante "
"unas semanas, permitiendo que nuestros civiles avanzaran sobre las arenas "
"relativamente sin obstáculos mientras nosotros seguíamos despejando el "
"camino. Intentamos compensar las pérdidas del clan lo mejor que pudimos, "
"intercambiando conocimientos, armas y objetos valiosos con los lugareños. Su "
"desconfianza y odio cedieron poco a poco ante un intercambio cultural más "
"pacífico — un resultado ventajoso para ambas partes.\n"
"\n"
"La larga marcha por el desierto atrajo la atención de muchos más habitantes "
"del desierto en la región, la mayoría temerosos de nuestro número, nuestras "
"armas, nuestros aliados... y nuestra especie. Sin embargo, una vez que la "
"curiosidad superó su temor inicial, algunos se acercaron a nosotros sin "
"malas intenciones. Mal Keshar consideró oportuno aprovechar esta situación."

#. [part]
#. NOTE: This whole block must match S5b's second story text block below.
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:116
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:139
msgid ""
"The more magically adept travelers chose to apprentice under Mal Keshar to "
"learn necromancy or hone their craft. Things quickly reached a point where "
"the lich’s minions nearly outnumbered our own capable spell casters... and "
"yet...\n"
"\n"
"But Mal Keshar was not the only one hiding something from me. Anlindë "
"refused to tell me about the previous trials faced by our kind at the hands "
"of the demons; Mal Keshar would tell me to ask Anlindë whenever I attempted "
"to inquire. I wondered if perhaps the Lady of Light and the Master of "
"Darkness would be willing to give me answers?"
msgstr ""
"Los viajeros con mayor aptitud mágica decidieron convertirse en aprendices "
"de Mal Keshar para aprender nigromancia o perfeccionar su arte. La situación "
"pronto llegó al punto en que los siervos del liche casi superaban en número "
"a nuestros propios lanzadores de hechizos... y aun así...\n"
"\n"
"Pero Mal Keshar no era el único que me ocultaba algo. Anlindë se negó a "
"contarme sobre las pruebas anteriores que nuestro pueblo enfrentó a manos de "
"los demonios; Mal Keshar me decía que preguntara a Anlindë cada vez que yo "
"intentaba indagar. Me preguntaba si tal vez la Dama de la Luz y el Maestro "
"de la Oscuridad estarían dispuestos a darme respuestas."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:121
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/05a_Crossfire.cfg:4
msgid "Crossfire"
msgstr "Fuego cruzado"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:122
msgid ""
"After some time we reached a river, which we then followed along the "
"southern shore. Small tributaries from the north gradually increased the "
"river’s speed and depth. The fresh water and the sparse vegetation thriving "
"along the riverbank seemed a sure sign that life, however little remained in "
"this harsh world, still existed outside our homeland. I was increasingly "
"eager to find the valley Mal Keshar mentioned in his instructions."
msgstr ""
"Al cabo de un tiempo llegamos a un río, que seguimos por la orilla sur. "
"Pequeños afluentes desde el norte aumentaban gradualmente la velocidad y "
"profundidad del río. El agua dulce y la escasa vegetación que prosperaba a "
"lo largo de la ribera parecían una señal clara de que la vida, por poca que "
"quedara en este mundo hostil, aún existía fuera de nuestra tierra natal. "
"Estaba cada vez más ansioso por encontrar el valle que Mal Keshar mencionó "
"en sus instrucciones."

#. [part]
#. NOTE: This block is the second paragraph from scenario 5a's first story text block.
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:133
msgid ""
"The long desert march drew the attention of many more desert dwellers in the "
"region, most of them fearful of our numbers, weapons, allies... and our "
"species. However, once curiosity overcame their initial fear, some of them "
"approached us with no ill intentions. Mal Keshar saw it fitting to take "
"advantage of this situation."
msgstr ""
"La larga marcha por el desierto atrajo la atención de muchos más habitantes "
"del desierto en la región, la mayoría temerosos de nuestro número, nuestras "
"armas, nuestros aliados... y nuestra especie. Sin embargo, una vez que la "
"curiosidad superó su temor inicial, algunos se acercaron a nosotros sin "
"malas intenciones. Mal Keshar consideró oportuno aprovechar esta situación."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:136
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/05b_Cursed_Plateau.cfg:4
msgid "Cursed Plateau"
msgstr "Meseta Maldita"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:151
msgid ""
"We continued northwest following the river, the mountains growing taller and "
"steeper. The green missing from the lowlands was all around us now; a new "
"hope filled our hearts as we saw how well the forest plants flourished "
"beneath the suns.\n"
"\n"
"If the armies of the Empire had claimed this corner of the world, they would "
"have no doubt defiled and destroyed this revivifying beauty for their unholy "
"feast. But there was something amiss about the whole situation. They were "
"adamant about stopping our march at all costs. They didn’t even give us an "
"opportunity to take prisoners. Their devotion to the supreme leader of their "
"realm and accursed names that were mostly unheard of amongst our kind seems "
"to be the sole drive for their existence."
msgstr ""
"Continuamos hacia el noroeste siguiendo el río, mientras las montañas se "
"volvían más altas y empinadas. El verdor que faltaba en las tierras bajas "
"ahora nos rodeaba; una nueva esperanza llenó nuestros corazones al ver cómo "
"las plantas del bosque florecían bajo los soles.\n"
"\n"
"Habíamos dejado atrás el desierto.\n"
"\n"
"Si los ejércitos del Imperio hubieran reclamado este rincón del mundo, sin "
"duda habrían profanado y destruido esta belleza revitalizadora para su impío "
"festín. Pero algo no encajaba en toda la situación. Eran implacables en su "
"intención de detener nuestra marcha a toda costa. Ni siquiera nos daban la "
"oportunidad de tomar prisioneros. Su devoción al líder supremo de su reino y "
"a nombres malditos, en su mayoría desconocidos para nuestra gente, parece "
"ser el único motor de su existencia."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:156
msgid ""
"‘Uria’, ‘Yechnagoth’... Other than Uria being a forgotten, fictitious symbol "
"of corruption and decay invented in a primeval epoch of superstition and "
"self-discovery, Anlindë knew nothing about the names.\n"
"\n"
"It suddenly occurred to me that our enemies could be seeking the same power "
"we did. Subverting or destroying the figures who wrought the last downfall "
"of the demons on Irdya would be a logical strategy, wouldn’t it? Especially "
"now that their bodies lie defenseless and frozen in time.\n"
"\n"
"Could that be the necromancer’s true intention as well? But..."
msgstr ""
"‘Uria’, ‘Yechnagoth’... Aparte de que Uria era un símbolo olvidado y "
"ficticio de corrupción y decadencia inventado en una época primitiva de "
"superstición y autodescubrimiento, Anlindë no sabía nada sobre esos "
"nombres.\n"
"\n"
"De repente se me ocurrió que nuestros enemigos podrían estar buscando el "
"mismo poder que nosotros. ¿No sería una estrategia lógica subvertir o "
"destruir a las figuras que causaron la última caída de los demonios en "
"Irdya? Especialmente ahora que sus cuerpos yacen indefensos y congelados en "
"el tiempo.\n"
"\n"
"¿Podría ser esa también la verdadera intención del nigromante? Pero..."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:163
msgid ""
"At times, Mal Keshar would stare at the river in silent contemplation. I "
"wondered for how long he had walked Irdya in undeath. What tales could he "
"tell? What scenes from ages past did he see where I saw but rushing water? "
"How would it be to walk the world for so long, to watch civilizations fall "
"and rise, to see everything you once knew destroyed, washed away like dust "
"after rain? Was there anything in the old world he truly missed?"
msgstr ""
"A veces, Mal Keshar se quedaba mirando el río en silenciosa contemplación. "
"Me preguntaba cuánto tiempo habría recorrido Irdya en su no-muerte. ¿Qué "
"historias podría contar? ¿Qué escenas de épocas pasadas veía él donde yo "
"sólo veía agua corriendo? ¿Cómo sería caminar por el mundo durante tanto "
"tiempo, ver civilizaciones caer y levantarse, ver cómo todo lo que alguna "
"vez conociste era destruido, barrido como polvo tras la lluvia? ¿Había algo "
"en el viejo mundo que realmente echara de menos?"

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:166
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/06_The_Moon_Valley.cfg:4
msgid "The Moon Valley"
msgstr "El valle Lunar"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:167
msgid ""
"We finally found the entrance to the fabled green valley. While at first the "
"pass seemed to be completely uninhabited, the keen eyes of our scouts could "
"discern some forlorn watch towers of crude construction."
msgstr ""
"Finalmente encontramos la entrada al legendario valle verde. Aunque al "
"principio el paso parecía estar completamente deshabitado, los ojos agudos "
"de nuestros exploradores pudieron discernir algunas torres de vigilancia "
"solitarias de tosca construcción."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:176
msgid ""
"And thus we entered the caves, leaving the bulk of our forces behind so we "
"could explore the place without risking catastrophic losses. None of us knew "
"for certain what kind of dangers lurked beneath the land said to be the "
"heart of Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Only Anlindë, the lich, and I planned on proceeding underground, but some of "
"our people would not hear of us going in alone and instead accompanied us "
"down into the darkness."
msgstr ""
"Y así entramos en las cuevas, dejando atrás a la mayor parte de nuestras "
"fuerzas para poder explorar el lugar sin arriesgar pérdidas catastróficas. "
"Ninguno de nosotros sabía con certeza qué clase de peligros acechaban bajo "
"la tierra, que se decía era el corazón de Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Sólo Anlindë, el liche y yo planeábamos continuar bajo tierra, pero algunos "
"de nuestros compañeros no quisieron oír hablar de que entráramos solos y en "
"cambio nos acompañaron en la oscuridad."

#. [part]
#. [unit]: type=Goliath, id=Goliath
#. [event]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:181
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/07_Goliath.cfg:712
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/07_Goliath.cfg:792
msgid "Goliath"
msgstr "Goliath"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:182
msgid ""
"According to our historians, multiple kingdoms of dwarves occupied the Heart "
"Mountains during the Golden Age, prosperous and powerful. Mal Keshar says "
"that all that came to an end when the humans of Wesnoth single-handedly "
"brought about the Fall.\n"
"\n"
"We had not ventured too deep underground when we began to find signs of a "
"recent civilization. Albeit in ruins, the entire place was adorned with fine "
"dwarvish architecture and handcraft. Could the dwarves have attempted to "
"reclaim their domains after so long? What kind of disaster might have struck "
"their efforts?\n"
"\n"
"Mal Keshar and Anlindë seemed uneasy about the whole situation."
msgstr ""
"Según nuestros historiadores, múltiples reinos enanos ocuparon las Montañas "
"Profundas durante la Edad Dorada, prósperos y poderosos. Mal Keshar dice que "
"todo eso llegó a su fin cuando los humanos de Wesnoth provocaron por sí "
"solos la Caída.\n"
"\n"
"No habíamos avanzado demasiado bajo tierra cuando empezamos a encontrar "
"señales de una civilización reciente. Aunque en ruinas, todo el lugar estaba "
"adornado con una fina arquitectura y artesanía enana. ¿Habrían intentado los "
"enanos reclamar sus dominios tras tanto tiempo? ¿Qué clase de desastre pudo "
"haber frustrado sus esfuerzos?\n"
"\n"
"Mal Keshar y Anlindë parecían incómodos con toda la situación."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:195
msgid ""
"After exploring for a while, we emerged at nightfall to tell our people to "
"follow us in. It was a difficult decision, but we feared leaving our poorly-"
"trained civilians between the pursuing scouts and the cliffs.\n"
"\n"
"The very thought of approaching the place where the Lady of Light and the "
"Master of Darkness had been seen for the last time was good for morale. It "
"was well that the ancient tale lit a flame in our hearts, for there was "
"little other light to be had in those forsaken tunnels."
msgstr ""
"Tras explorar un rato, emergimos al anochecer para decirle a nuestro pueblo "
"que nos siguiera dentro. Fue una decisión difícil, pero temíamos dejar a "
"nuestros civiles mal entrenados entre los exploradores que nos perseguían y "
"los acantilados.\n"
"\n"
"El mero pensamiento de acercarnos al lugar donde se vio por última vez a la "
"Dama de la Luz y al Maestro de la Oscuridad levantó la moral. Menos mal que "
"la antigua leyenda encendió una llama en nuestros corazones, porque había "
"poca otra luz en esos túneles malditos."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:200
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/08_Errand_of_Hope.cfg:4
msgid "An Errand of Hope"
msgstr "Una búsqueda de esperanza"

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:200
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/08x_A_Royal_Meeting.cfg:4
msgid "Royal Meeting"
msgstr "Reunión Real"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:201
msgid ""
"As we went deeper and deeper, the contrived openings in the ceiling that "
"permitted us a scarce beam of sunlight diminished until they vanished "
"entirely. By contrast, the subterranean water streams became more abundant, "
"both in quantity and volume. Oh, the irony! In the caves we had all the "
"water we had so sorely lacked in the desert, but we had to struggle to see "
"our steps.\n"
"\n"
"Under the world’s skies we could see the moon tracing out its cycle by night "
"— by day, the suns would announce the time. Here we had no notion of how "
"much time was passing as we traveled underground. It was as if time itself "
"had been frozen and bound to the rocks."
msgstr ""
"A medida que nos adentrábamos más y más, las aberturas artificiales en el "
"techo que nos permitían un escaso rayo de luz solar se fueron reduciendo "
"hasta desaparecer por completo. En contraste, los arroyos subterráneos se "
"volvieron más abundantes, tanto en cantidad como en volumen. ¡Oh, la ironía! "
"En las cuevas teníamos toda el agua que tanto nos había faltado en el "
"desierto, pero teníamos que esforzarnos para ver dónde poníamos los pies.\n"
"\n"
"Bajo los cielos del mundo podíamos ver a la luna trazar su ciclo por la "
"noche — de día, los soles nos marcaban la hora. Aquí no teníamos noción "
"alguna de cuánto tiempo pasaba mientras viajábamos bajo tierra. Era como si "
"el tiempo mismo hubiese quedado congelado y atado a las rocas."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:212
msgid ""
"This dwarf, Althurin by name, led us through curving tunnels that opened "
"upon a great cavern. There lay a sprawling city, the capital of their "
"kingdom.\n"
"\n"
"This greedy race was one tremendously despised by many of our ancestors due "
"in part to their disinterest in protecting the beautiful and green places of "
"their world. Indeed, it was said amongst us that the dwarves would destroy "
"Irdya’s beauty for wealth and power. And yet, their masons shaped structures "
"of great beauty from rock, their smiths fashioned marvelous wonders out of "
"metal and other materials they found underground — these were things that we "
"elves could not help but admire."
msgstr ""
"Este enano, de nombre Althurin, nos guió a través de túneles curvos que se "
"abrían hacia una gran caverna. Allí se extendía una ciudad enorme, la "
"capital de su reino.\n"
"\n"
"Esta raza codiciosa fue tremendamente despreciada por muchos de nuestros "
"antepasados, en parte por su desinterés en proteger los hermosos y verdes "
"lugares de su mundo. En efecto, se decía entre nosotros que los enanos "
"destruirían la belleza de Irdya por riqueza y poder. Y sin embargo, sus "
"canteros moldeaban estructuras de gran belleza a partir de la roca, sus "
"herreros forjaban maravillas extraordinarias con metales y otros materiales "
"que encontraban bajo tierra — cosas que nosotros, los elfos, no podíamos "
"evitar admirar."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:217
msgid ""
"Their mastery of ancient magic was also remarkable. By carving runes onto "
"surfaces such as shields, hammers, or even walls, and imbuing them with a "
"force not understood by even the mightiest elven sorcerers, they could work "
"powerful and complex spells. Some of these rune-workings were used in "
"defensive structures against enemies, and had to be temporarily suppressed "
"in order to allow Anlindë and the lich access into the heart of the city — "
"the castle of the King."
msgstr ""
"Su dominio de la magia ancestral también era notable. Al tallar runas en "
"superficies como escudos, martillos o incluso paredes, e imbuirlas con una "
"fuerza que ni siquiera los más poderosos hechiceros élficos comprendían, "
"podían realizar conjuros poderosos y complejos. Algunas de estas runas se "
"utilizaban en estructuras defensivas contra los enemigos, y tuvieron que ser "
"temporalmente desactivadas para permitir a Anlindë y al liche el acceso al "
"corazón de la ciudad: el castillo del Rey."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:226
msgid ""
"Certainly, as Althurin said, we would encounter all sorts of exotic "
"creatures that could only thrive in the eternal shadows of Irdya. Most were "
"understandably frightened by our presence. From their perspective, we were "
"invaders, terrifying monsters who could end their pitiful lives in an "
"instant with our fire and magic. But unlike the invaders we had faced in our "
"Valley, we did not intend to harm or kill every living thing standing in our "
"way."
msgstr ""
"Sin duda, como dijo Althurin, nos encontraríamos con toda clase de criaturas "
"exóticas que sólo podían prosperar en las sombras eternas de Irdya. La "
"mayoría estaba comprensiblemente aterrorizada por nuestra presencia. Desde "
"su perspectiva, éramos invasores, monstruos aterradores que podían acabar "
"con sus miserables vidas en un instante con nuestro fuego y magia. Pero a "
"diferencia de los invasores que habíamos enfrentado en nuestro Valle, no "
"teníamos la intención de dañar o matar a todo ser vivo que se interpusiera "
"en nuestro camino."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:229
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/09_The_Library.cfg:4
msgid "The Library"
msgstr "La Biblioteca"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:230
msgid ""
"Deeper and deeper we went, through the labyrinthine dark caverns, until we "
"reached the igneous passages that the late mentor of our dwarf guide first "
"found for us."
msgstr ""
"Nos adentramos más y más en las laberínticas cavernas oscuras, hasta que "
"llegamos a los pasajes ígneos que el difunto maestro de nuestro guía enano "
"había descubierto para nosotros."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:239
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/10_The_Source_of_Light.cfg:4
msgid "The Source of Light"
msgstr "La fuente de luz"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:256
msgid ""
"The Lady of Light seemed and acted less like a majestic elven sorceress of "
"untold might and more like a young nymph of the forests, her luminous aspect "
"notwithstanding. Anlindë said that she had always been more closely bound to "
"our faerie nature than other elves, and hence for most of her life she "
"frequented the wilderness, away from civilization. This became more evident "
"as her harsh exterior slowly gave way to her true self, as we all shared "
"stories and experiences on the long way back to Herthgar’s capital.\n"
"\n"
"I do not know if it is because I had always been the reserved sort and never "
"met many women outside the circles of my duty, or because our race changed "
"over generations in some way that was not evident to the eye; whichever the "
"case is, I found the Lady of Light alluring, like a dream of an age long "
"gone. I wondered if every elf was as radiant as her back in the Golden Age."
msgstr ""
"La Dama de la Luz parecía y actuaba menos como una majestuosa hechicera "
"élfica de poder incalculable y más como una joven ninfa de los bosques, a "
"pesar de su aspecto luminoso. Anlindë dijo que siempre había estado más "
"estrechamente unida a nuestra naturaleza feérica que otros elfos, y por eso "
"pasó la mayor parte de su vida frecuentando la naturaleza, lejos de la "
"civilización. Esto se hizo más evidente a medida que su duro exterior cedía "
"lentamente para mostrar su verdadero ser, mientras todos compartíamos "
"historias y experiencias en el largo camino de regreso a la capital de "
"Herthgar.\n"
"\n"
"No sé si se debe a que siempre fui una persona reservada y nunca conocí a "
"muchas mujeres fuera de los círculos de mi deber, o a que nuestra raza "
"cambió con los siglos de una forma que no es evidente a simple vista; sea "
"cual sea el caso, encontré a la Dama de la Luz cautivadora, como un sueño de "
"una era ya lejana. Me pregunté si todos los elfos eran tan radiantes como "
"ella en la Edad Dorada."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:261
msgid ""
"But her mystifying appearance was merely a distraction for the unwary, for "
"those who had not yet heard her name or accounts of her legendary feats. "
"Soon, we would bear witness to her combat prowess, and learn how fierce and "
"frightening she could be as the situation demanded.\n"
"\n"
"Because, once we neared Herthgar’s capital, we saw not the bustling dwarven "
"settlements that welcomed us after saving Althurin and his men from doom; "
"instead, what we saw were Anlindë’s fears, realized in our absence."
msgstr ""
"Pero su enigmática apariencia no era más que una distracción para los "
"incautos, para aquellos que aún no habían oído su nombre ni relatos de sus "
"legendarias proezas. Pronto seríamos testigos de su destreza en combate, y "
"aprenderíamos lo feroz y aterradora que podía ser cuando la situación lo "
"exigía.\n"
"\n"
"Porque, una vez que nos acercamos a la capital de Herthgar, no vimos los "
"bulliciosos asentamientos enanos que nos dieron la bienvenida tras salvar a "
"Althurin y a sus hombres de la perdición; en cambio, lo que vimos fueron los "
"temores de Anlindë, hechos realidad en nuestra ausencia."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:267
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/11_Strike_on_Herthgar.cfg:4
msgid "Strike on Herthgar"
msgstr "Ataque sobre Herthgar"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:268
msgid "We made haste towards the keep, in fear that we had arrived too late..."
msgstr ""
"Nos apresuramos hacia la fortaleza, temiendo haber llegado demasiado tarde..."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:277
msgid ""
"After that exchange, I stayed behind in the dwarven throne room, and talked "
"to Anlindë a last time before bidding her farewell.\n"
"\n"
"She had always been there to guide me since my father’s death. Even now, at "
"the premature end of our journey together, she imparted her wisdom to me. "
"She spoke of our past leaders and the sacrifices they had to make for the "
"sake of others; the great losses suffered by Telchior’s people before "
"finding the Valley; the pact with Zhangor; the story of Kalenz and Landar; "
"the betrayal of the humans and the war with the orcs..."
msgstr ""
"Después de aquel intercambio, me quedé atrás en la sala del trono enana y "
"hablé con Anlindë por última vez antes de despedirme de ella.\n"
"\n"
"Siempre había estado allí para guiarme desde la muerte de mi padre. Incluso "
"ahora, en el prematuro final de nuestro viaje juntos, me impartió su "
"sabiduría. Me habló de nuestros antiguos líderes y de los sacrificios que "
"tuvieron que hacer por el bien de los demás; de las grandes pérdidas "
"sufridas por el pueblo de Telchior antes de encontrar el Valle; del pacto "
"con Zhangor; de la historia de Kalenz y Landar; de la traición de los "
"humanos y de la guerra con los orcos..."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:282
msgid ""
"But I could barely retain any of that, for my heart was too fraught with "
"grief to pay heed to her words.\n"
"\n"
"Once we had nothing more left to say, I left the room only to find a pair of "
"dispassionate amber orbs waiting behind the doors. I did my best to ignore "
"Lady Elynia and continued ahead, hoping her eyes did not spy the tears in my "
"own."
msgstr ""
"Pero apenas pude retener nada de eso, porque mi corazón estaba demasiado "
"cargado de pena como para prestar atención a sus palabras.\n"
"\n"
"Una vez que no tuvimos nada más que decirnos, salí de la sala sólo para "
"encontrar un par de orbes ámbar impasibles esperándome tras las puertas. "
"Hice todo lo posible por ignorar a Lady Elynia y seguí adelante, esperando "
"que sus ojos no vieran las lágrimas en los míos."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:287
msgid ""
"Even though Anlindë had kept such dark secrets from me all these years, I "
"could not resent her. First Mal Keshar, and then Anlindë... Perhaps I am too "
"easily forgiving to be the kind of leader Lédinor and Anlindë expected.\n"
"\n"
"Will this never end? How many more will have to give up their lives to "
"protect the rest of us from the Chaos Empire and the demons of Uria?"
msgstr ""
"Aunque Anlindë me había ocultado tales secretos oscuros durante todos estos "
"años, no podía guardar resentimiento hacia ella. Primero Mal Keshar, y luego "
"Anlindë... Quizás soy demasiado indulgente para ser el tipo de líder que "
"Lédinor y Anlindë esperaban.\n"
"\n"
"¿Nunca terminará esto? ¿Cuántos más tendrán que dar sus vidas para "
"protegernos del Imperio del Caos y de los demonios de Uria?"

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:292
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/12_The_Escape.cfg:4
msgid "The Escape"
msgstr "El escape"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:293
msgid ""
"I longed for the return of peace. I desperately wanted to get away from the "
"incessant strife and bloodshed and find a new home in one of the remaining "
"forests, or even the underground.\n"
"\n"
"I was absorbed in those foolish thoughts when, suddenly, reason came back to "
"me; and then I knew what ought to be my next mission.\n"
"\n"
"Because even in the deep darkness of Irdya’s fractured heart, we still had "
"the guidance of the Lady of Light and our hope on our side; and I knew there "
"had to be a way to throw the Empire into utter disarray so it would wither "
"and die like its predecessor did."
msgstr ""
"Anhelaba el regreso de la paz. Deseaba desesperadamente escapar de la lucha "
"incesante y del derramamiento de sangre, y encontrar un nuevo hogar en uno "
"de los bosques que aún quedaban... o incluso bajo tierra.\n"
"\n"
"Estaba absorto en esos pensamientos necios cuando, de repente, la razón "
"volvió a mí; y entonces supe cuál debía ser mi próxima misión.\n"
"\n"
"Porque incluso en la profunda oscuridad del corazón fracturado de Irdya, aún "
"teníamos la guía de la Dama de la Luz y la esperanza de nuestro lado; y "
"sabía que debía haber una forma de sumir al Imperio en un caos absoluto para "
"que se marchitara y muriera como lo hizo su predecesor."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:306
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/13_Face_your_Fate.cfg:4
msgid "Face your Fate"
msgstr "Enfrenta tu destino"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:316
msgid ""
"What lay in front of us was unlike anything I ever had imagined: it was not "
"simply a small valley guarding its green life from the scorching suns, but "
"rather an endless expanse of vegetated lands. It was like being home "
"again... No — the scenery was more akin to a dreamland conjured from the "
"memories of a long gone age.\n"
"\n"
"The Lady of Light had not seen such a landscape for hundreds, thousands, "
"perhaps millions, of years, and she rejoiced at the view while the fresh "
"northern winds blew in her face. The dwarves, on the other hand, were too "
"used to their underground abodes to feel at ease on the surface. I "
"understood them, and regretted that we could not have their company for our "
"next journey. The prospect of marching into the northern humans’ territory "
"uninvited was not very encouraging."
msgstr ""
"Lo que teníamos delante no se parecía en nada a lo que jamás había "
"imaginado: no era simplemente un pequeño valle protegiendo su vida verde de "
"los soles abrasadores, sino una vasta extensión interminable de tierras "
"cubiertas de vegetación. Era como estar en casa otra vez... No — el paisaje "
"era más bien semejante a una tierra de ensueño evocada de los recuerdos de "
"una era ya ida.\n"
"\n"
"La Dama de la Luz no había visto un paisaje así en cientos, miles, quizás "
"millones de años, y se regocijaba ante la vista mientras los frescos vientos "
"del norte acariciaban su rostro. Los enanos, en cambio, estaban demasiado "
"acostumbrados a sus moradas subterráneas como para sentirse a gusto en la "
"superficie. Los entendía, y lamentaba que no pudiésemos contar con su "
"compañía para nuestro próximo viaje. La perspectiva de marchar hacia el "
"territorio de los humanos del norte sin ser invitados no resultaba muy "
"alentadora."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:321
msgid "Bye and Behold"
msgstr "Adiós y contemplad"

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:321
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/14x_The_Aragwaithi.cfg:4
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/14y_The_Grand_Council.cfg:4
msgid "The Grand Council"
msgstr "El Gran Consejo"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:322
msgid ""
"I knew that from that point onwards, I would have to make decisions for our "
"people on my own, as Anlindë was no longer there to provide me with her — "
"seldom unwise — counsel and guidance. And I knew there was a possibility "
"that I might come to regret some of those decisions. But someone had to take "
"the reins of our fractured civilization and move us forward. And that "
"someone, at least for the moment, had to be me."
msgstr ""
"Sabía que, a partir de ese momento, tendría que tomar decisiones por mi "
"cuenta para nuestro pueblo, ya que Anlindë ya no estaba allí para brindarme "
"su —rara vez desacertado— consejo y guía. Y también sabía que existía la "
"posibilidad de que llegara a lamentar algunas de esas decisiones. Pero "
"alguien tenía que tomar las riendas de nuestra civilización fracturada y "
"hacernos avanzar. Y ese alguien, al menos por ahora, debía ser yo."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:331
msgid ""
"Many of us grew up listening to horror stories about savage humans who "
"murdered every living creature in sight to procure food. Nobody ever "
"suspected that far beyond our domains some of them had gathered to build "
"such an impressive civilization ruled not by force, but rather by wisdom.\n"
"\n"
"The Aragwaith country was governed not by a single person, but rather by a "
"council representing communities from every corner of the Far North. Instead "
"of scavengers, there were farmers and ranchers, smiths and carpenters, "
"builders and architects, and so on. Their military arm was a well-organized "
"and highly-trained body, practical experience nonwhistanding; it had not "
"seen serious conflict in over a century. Theirs was a peaceful and "
"prosperous civilization, a hard-won luxury, one seeded by the bones of "
"tyrants past and watered with the bloodshed of countless wars."
msgstr ""
"Muchos de nosotros crecimos escuchando historias de terror sobre humanos "
"salvajes que asesinaban a toda criatura viviente a la vista para procurarse "
"alimento. Nadie sospechaba que, mucho más allá de nuestros dominios, algunos "
"de ellos se habían reunido para construir una civilización tan "
"impresionante, gobernada no por la fuerza, sino por la sabiduría.\n"
"\n"
"El país de los Aragwaith no era gobernado por una sola persona, sino por un "
"consejo que representaba a comunidades de todos los rincones del Lejano "
"Norte. En lugar de carroñeros, había agricultores y ganaderos, herreros y "
"carpinteros, constructores y arquitectos, y así sucesivamente. Su brazo "
"militar era un cuerpo bien organizado y altamente entrenado, aunque con poca "
"experiencia práctica; no había visto un conflicto serio en más de un siglo. "
"Era una civilización pacífica y próspera, un lujo arduamente conquistado, "
"sembrado con los huesos de tiranos del pasado y regado con la sangre de "
"incontables guerras."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:336
msgid ""
"Such was the extent of the country’s success after the civil war that even "
"orc merchants from the western regions and coasts of the Great Continent "
"were allowed within its borders. Mal Keshar did not take kindly to the "
"sight, but Elynia reminded me that there was a time when the human kingdoms "
"comprising the old Empire had fruitful relations with the orcish clans of "
"the Far North.\n"
"\n"
"Bearing witness to the wonders of civilization rekindled my faith in Irdya’s "
"ability to heal its profound wounds after the Fall. There was simply no way "
"we could allow the dark forces of Uria to take all this from us. I knew what "
"had to be done — the matter was deciding upon an approach that would not "
"result in our self-destruction.\n"
"\n"
"So I gathered as much information as possible from Erathan and his men, "
"rehearsed my plan, and prepared for the inevitable meeting with the Grand "
"Council. And, as much as it pained me, I decided to keep it secret from "
"Elynia and Mal Keshar, at least for the time being."
msgstr ""
"Tal era el grado de éxito del país tras la guerra civil que incluso "
"mercaderes orcos de las regiones occidentales y de las costas del Gran "
"Continente tenían permitida la entrada en sus fronteras. A Mal Keshar no le "
"agradó la visión, pero Elynia me recordó que hubo un tiempo en que los "
"reinos humanos que formaban el antiguo Imperio mantenían relaciones "
"fructíferas con los clanes orcos del Lejano Norte.\n"
"\n"
"Ser testigo de las maravillas de la civilización reavivó mi fe en la "
"capacidad de Irdya para sanar sus profundas heridas tras la Caída. "
"Simplemente no podíamos permitir que las fuerzas oscuras de Uria nos "
"arrebataran todo esto. Sabía lo que debía hacerse; la cuestión era decidir "
"un enfoque que no resultara en nuestra autodestrucción.\n"
"\n"
"Así que reuní toda la información posible de Erathan y sus hombres, repasé "
"mi plan y me preparé para la inevitable reunión con el Gran Consejo. Y, por "
"mucho que me doliera, decidí mantenerlo en secreto para Elynia y Mal "
"Keshar... al menos por ahora."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:344
msgid ""
"Eventually we arrived at the outskirts of Raelthyn, the northern capital. "
"Even from a distance, the city was far larger than any other northern "
"settlements we had seen thus far. Dominating the landscape was a tall, "
"ominous castle."
msgstr ""
"Finalmente llegamos a las afueras de Raelthyn, la capital del norte. Incluso "
"desde la distancia, la ciudad era mucho más grande que cualquier otro "
"asentamiento norteño que hubiéramos visto hasta entonces. Dominando el "
"paisaje se alzaba un castillo alto y ominoso."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:354
msgid ""
"We rested for that night in the safety and hospitality of Raelthyn — or at "
"least, most of us did. Having spent so many months on the field sleeping in "
"crude sacks at night, I felt uncomfortable on the luxurious metal beds that "
"civilization had to offer. Every once in a while I would get up and see "
"Elynia standing or sitting on a nearby balcony, gazing at the moon. I felt "
"compelled to go talk to her, but I knew there was nothing I could say to "
"remedy the situation. The best I could do was to try and open up to her "
"later once her resentment subsided.\n"
"\n"
"When dawn broke, we immediately prepared for our journey into orcish "
"territory. I had to confront Elynia’s eyes again. Truth to be told, when we "
"first met I never thought those gentle amber orbs could hold such contempt "
"towards a living creature."
msgstr ""
"Pasamos esa noche en la seguridad y hospitalidad de Raelthyn — o al menos, "
"la mayoría de nosotros lo hizo. Tras haber pasado tantos meses en el campo "
"durmiendo en sacos toscos, me sentía incómodo en las lujosas camas metálicas "
"que la civilización tenía para ofrecer. De vez en cuando me levantaba y veía "
"a Elynia de pie o sentada en un balcón cercano, contemplando la luna. Me "
"sentía impulsado a ir a hablarle, pero sabía que no había nada que pudiera "
"decir para remediar la situación. Lo mejor que podía hacer era intentar "
"abrirme con ella más adelante, una vez que su resentimiento se hubiera "
"disipado.\n"
"\n"
"Cuando amaneció, nos preparamos de inmediato para nuestro viaje hacia "
"territorio orco. Tuve que enfrentar nuevamente los ojos de Elynia. A decir "
"verdad, cuando nos conocimos nunca pensé que esos gentiles orbes ámbar "
"pudieran albergar tal desprecio hacia una criatura viviente."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:359
msgid ""
"To keep us in check, the Grand Council assigned us Erathan and a few other "
"men — all highly skilled with the bow and arrow — under the pretense of "
"protecting us from any potential attempts against our lives.\n"
"\n"
"Even though Mal Keshar would disagree with me, it did not seem like the orcs "
"ever considered causing any harm to us. At most they seemed displeased by "
"the Council’s choice of diplomats, as well as the fact that they hardly knew "
"anything about our race and origins. But our insistence paid off in the end. "
"We were finally granted an audience with Quogar Ratham, the local orcish "
"chieftain."
msgstr ""
"Para mantenernos vigilados, el Gran Consejo nos asignó a Erathan y a unos "
"pocos hombres más —todos ellos altamente hábiles con el arco y la flecha— "
"bajo el pretexto de protegernos de cualquier posible atentado contra "
"nuestras vidas.\n"
"\n"
"Aunque Mal Keshar no estaría de acuerdo conmigo, no parecía que los orcos "
"hubieran considerado en ningún momento hacernos daño. A lo sumo, parecían "
"molestos por la elección de diplomáticos del Consejo, así como por el hecho "
"de que apenas sabían nada sobre nuestra raza y orígenes. Pero nuestra "
"insistencia dio sus frutos al final. Finalmente se nos concedió una "
"audiencia con Quogar Ratham, el caudillo orco local."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:364
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/15_Shadows_of_Time.cfg:4
msgid "Shadows of Time"
msgstr "Sombras del tiempo"

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:364
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/15x_Parting_Ways.cfg:4
msgid "Parting Ways"
msgstr "Caminos Separados"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:365
msgid ""
"Of all the things that I had been through during this twisting journey "
"across the continent, playing ambassador to an orcish chieftain was amongst "
"the most bizarre of them. We had gone from killing orcs on the sands without "
"a single thought to having relatively amicable conversations with their kin "
"in the west.\n"
"\n"
"Little did I suspect then how things would soon take a darker turn."
msgstr ""
"De todas las cosas por las que había pasado durante este sinuoso viaje a "
"través del continente, hacer de embajador ante un caudillo orco fue una de "
"las más extrañas. Habíamos pasado de matar orcos en las arenas sin pensarlo "
"dos veces a mantener conversaciones relativamente cordiales con sus "
"parientes del oeste.\n"
"\n"
"Poco sospechaba entonces cómo las cosas pronto tomarían un giro más oscuro."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:377
msgid ""
"We spent the next few weeks resting in the peaceful Aragwaith capital, "
"gathering intelligence on our target and making preparations for our final "
"mission. Since we feared that they might refuse to sign the alliance pact "
"otherwise, we kept our plans a secret from the Council.\n"
"\n"
"As time passed on, the border skirmishes grew in number and intensity, and "
"the Far North denizens began to take the threat more seriously. The timing "
"could not be more convenient, as the news of the Chaos Empire’s hostile "
"advances helped quell the humans’ instinctive distrust of our kind. To think "
"that there once was an era when elves were the custodians of the Great "
"Continent rather than humans..."
msgstr ""
"Pasamos las semanas siguientes descansando en la pacífica capital de los "
"Aragwaith, recopilando información sobre nuestro objetivo y haciendo los "
"preparativos para nuestra misión final. Como temíamos que de otro modo se "
"negaran a firmar el pacto de alianza, mantuvimos nuestros planes en secreto "
"para el Consejo.\n"
"\n"
"Con el paso del tiempo, las escaramuzas en la frontera aumentaron en número "
"e intensidad, y los habitantes del Lejano Norte empezaron a tomarse la "
"amenaza más en serio. El momento no podía ser más conveniente, pues las "
"noticias sobre los avances hostiles del Imperio del Caos ayudaron a aplacar "
"la desconfianza instintiva de los humanos hacia los de nuestra clase. Pensar "
"que hubo una época en la que los elfos eran los custodios del Gran "
"Continente en lugar de los humanos..."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:383
msgid ""
"Finally, the decisive day came and the entire Council gathered once more to "
"decide our destiny."
msgstr ""
"Finalmente, llegó el día decisivo y el Consejo entero se reunió una vez más "
"para decidir nuestro destino."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:392
msgid ""
"Throughout Irdya’s relatively short recorded history, elves seldom "
"participated in wars. On the few occasions they did, the results were grim "
"and devastating for everyone involved: the orc invasion following the "
"humans’ arrival, a civil war amongst our forefathers, a war against an "
"empire led by a great Necromancer, and the final doom of Wesmere under "
"Zhangor’s rule.\n"
"\n"
"We had agreed that our sacrifice was necessary to keep the elves’ "
"involvement in this new war to a minimum. Lord Inodien and Lady Unarye would "
"see that our people would not be senselessly dispatched to the battlefield "
"to die. Meanwhile, Elynia, Mal Keshar and I would hopefully earn our people "
"a swift victory by bringing down the orchestrator of our suffering, the "
"brain behind the machine that is the Chaos Empire."
msgstr ""
"A lo largo de la relativamente corta historia registrada de Irdya, los elfos "
"raras veces participaron en guerras. En las pocas ocasiones en que lo "
"hicieron, los resultados fueron sombríos y devastadores para todos los "
"involucrados: la invasión orca tras la llegada de los humanos, una guerra "
"civil entre nuestros antepasados, una guerra contra un imperio liderado por "
"un gran Nigromante, y la perdición final de Wesmere bajo el gobierno de "
"Zhangor.\n"
"\n"
"Habíamos acordado que nuestro sacrificio era necesario para mantener la "
"participación de los elfos en esta nueva guerra al mínimo. Lord Inodien y "
"Lady Unarye se encargarían de que nuestro pueblo no fuese enviado sin "
"sentido al campo de batalla para morir. Mientras tanto, Elynia, Mal Keshar y "
"yo esperaríamos ganar para nuestro pueblo una victoria rápida derribando al "
"orquestador de nuestro sufrimiento, la mente tras la máquina que es el "
"Imperio del Caos."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:397
msgid ""
"I wondered if we would ever return to the northern country as victors; "
"whether we would become stranded in enemy territory and die before "
"accomplishing our mission, or be killed by the demons after vanquishing "
"their leader.\n"
"\n"
"Even though the Aragwaithi had gathered enough information on our target to "
"guide us on our mission, there were still many questions left to answer. "
"Most importantly, are we to believe that Uria actually exists and is behind "
"everything? Could Yechnagoth have survived the battle against our desert kin "
"somehow? Did Anlindë manage to vanquish the Warlord, or was her sacrifice in "
"vain? Could she be alive in a dungeon somewhere, tortured by our enemies, or "
"would she have taken her own life before?"
msgstr ""
"Me preguntaba si alguna vez regresaríamos al país del norte como vencedores; "
"si quedaríamos varados en territorio enemigo y moriríamos antes de cumplir "
"nuestra misión, o si seríamos asesinados por los demonios tras derrotar a su "
"líder.\n"
"\n"
"Aunque los Aragwaithi habían reunido suficiente información sobre nuestro "
"objetivo para guiarnos en nuestra misión, aún quedaban muchas preguntas por "
"responder. Lo más importante: ¿debíamos creer que Uria realmente existe y "
"está detrás de todo? ¿Podría Yechnagoth haber sobrevivido de algún modo a la "
"batalla contra nuestros parientes del desierto? ¿Logró Anlindë vencer al "
"Señor de la Guerra, o fue su sacrificio en vano? ¿Podría estar viva en algún "
"calabozo, torturada por nuestros enemigos, o se habría quitado la vida antes?"

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:402
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/16_Dawn_of_War.cfg:4
msgid "Dawn of War"
msgstr "El amanecer de la guerra"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:403
msgid ""
"But there was one thing we did know for sure: this was the beginning of the "
"end, the dawn of our war against the Empire of Chaos. Us three were at the "
"center of the storm, and we would make sure the Empire and Uria herself "
"would feel the wrath of the peoples of Irdya."
msgstr ""
"Pero había una cosa que sí sabíamos con certeza: este era el principio del "
"fin, el amanecer de nuestra guerra contra el Imperio del Caos. Nosotros tres "
"estábamos en el centro de la tormenta, y nos aseguraríamos de que el Imperio "
"y la propia Uria sintieran la ira de los pueblos de Irdya."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:412
msgid ""
"And thus the long march began.\n"
"\n"
"We were warned that these mountains were treacherous and rife with hostile "
"creatures, but the sight of more of those metallic birds flying about still "
"proved a surprise. They seemed to roam freely across the land without a "
"particular purpose, as if they had become part of the local fauna. Perhaps "
"they were once part of the many experiments the Chaos Empire performed on "
"living creatures... even persons."
msgstr ""
"Y así comenzó la larga marcha.\n"
"\n"
"Se nos advirtió que estas montañas eran traicioneras y estaban llenas de "
"criaturas hostiles, pero la vista de más de aquellas aves metálicas volando "
"por allí aún resultó sorprendente. Parecían deambular libremente por la "
"tierra sin un propósito en particular, como si se hubieran convertido en "
"parte de la fauna local. Quizás alguna vez fueron parte de los muchos "
"experimentos que el Imperio del Caos realizó sobre criaturas vivas... "
"incluso personas."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:417
msgid ""
"Although we had spent much time together since we found her in the Heart "
"Mountains, it was only now that I noticed an odd habit Elynia had: she much "
"preferred to walk like us commoners than to float above ground as other "
"elves or faeries possessing the capability did.\n"
"\n"
"Out of curiosity and lacking anything better to speak of, I decided to ask "
"her about this peculiar habit. She revealed she has done this for as long as "
"she remembers, perhaps because her mentor and guardian did as well. It was "
"then that it occurred to me that I knew nothing of Elynia’s past life in the "
"Golden Age beyond her history lessons. I wondered if her childhood had been "
"like mine, with her guardian taking over for her missing parents."
msgstr ""
"Aunque habíamos pasado mucho tiempo juntos desde que la encontramos en las "
"Montañas Profundas, solo ahora me di cuenta de un extraño hábito que tenía "
"Elynia: prefería caminar como nosotros los comunes, en vez de flotar sobre "
"el suelo como otros elfos o hadas con esa capacidad.\n"
"\n"
"Por curiosidad y sin nada mejor de qué hablar, decidí preguntarle sobre este "
"peculiar hábito. Ella reveló que lo hacía desde que podía recordar, quizá "
"porque su mentor y guardián también lo hacía. Fue entonces cuando me di "
"cuenta de que no sabía nada sobre la vida pasada de Elynia en la Edad Dorada "
"más allá de sus lecciones de historia. Me pregunté si su infancia habría "
"sido como la mía, con su guardián ocupando el lugar de sus padres ausentes."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:422
msgid ""
"She gazed at me, her eyes as alluring as the setting sun. Then she smiled, "
"and I saw for a brief moment a glimpse of something else hiding beneath the "
"surface.\n"
"\n"
"I decided to not ask her about her mentor, for fear of bringing back sad "
"memories. Like Mal Keshar, she has lived for longer than any other creature "
"on Irdya, and seems intent on leaving her past behind."
msgstr ""
"Me miró, con sus ojos tan cautivadores como el sol poniente. Luego sonrió, y "
"vi por un breve instante un atisbo de algo más oculto bajo la superficie.\n"
"\n"
"Decidí no preguntarle sobre su mentor, por miedo a traer de vuelta recuerdos "
"tristes. Como Mal Keshar, ella ha vivido más tiempo que cualquier otra "
"criatura en Irdya, y parece decidida a dejar atrás su pasado."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:427
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/17_Voice_of_the_Armageddon.cfg:4
msgid "Voice of the Armageddon"
msgstr "La Voz del Armagedón"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:428
msgid ""
"Two days into our journey, we came across a road quite evidently built by "
"our enemies amidst the tall mountains not long ago. A new confrontation was "
"imminent."
msgstr ""
"Dos días después de iniciar nuestro viaje, nos topamos con un camino que, a "
"todas luces, había sido construido por nuestros enemigos en medio de las "
"altas montañas no hacía mucho. Una nueva confrontación era inminente."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:438
msgid ""
"Following our second encounter with the vile necromancer, we felt less "
"inclined to stop to rest and sleep during the night. Most of the demons we "
"had encountered thus far seemed more adept at fighting in the darkness than "
"under daylight. Moreover, we did not know for certain if Hekuba could be "
"watching us from afar, planning his next strike; it would not do us any good "
"to suffer more casualties before reaching our objective.\n"
"\n"
"After only a couple of days, we succumbed to the fatigue and set up camp "
"during the long dark."
msgstr ""
"Tras nuestro segundo encuentro con el vil nigromante, nos sentimos menos "
"inclinados a detenernos para descansar y dormir durante la noche. La mayoría "
"de los demonios que habíamos encontrado hasta entonces parecían más diestros "
"luchando en la oscuridad que a la luz del día. Además, no sabíamos con "
"certeza si Hekuba podía estar vigilándonos desde lejos, planeando su próximo "
"ataque; no nos convenía sufrir más bajas antes de alcanzar nuestro "
"objetivo.\n"
"\n"
"Tras solo un par de días, sucumbimos al cansancio y montamos campamento "
"durante la larga oscuridad."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:443
msgid ""
"Sleeping was not an easy task. Even though we were tired and perfectly able "
"to drift off in a matter of seconds, we had to take turns watching over the "
"encampment while others slept. Mal Keshar, of course, made sure to keep us "
"awake during each shift telling us stories of his past feats; rather "
"unfortunately for us, most of them involved the deaths of innocent — and "
"sometimes not-so-innocent — people described in vivid detail.\n"
"\n"
"We continued to use the same strategy every night afterwards, with Elynia "
"taking over for Mal Keshar at times to keep our living companions "
"entertained with less grisly anecdotes. She boasted that she did not need to "
"sleep as often or for as long as most of us normal people, but as I came to "
"witness, that was simply not true."
msgstr ""
"Dormir no era tarea fácil. Aunque estábamos cansados y perfectamente capaces "
"de quedarnos dormidos en cuestión de segundos, debíamos turnarnos para "
"vigilar el campamento mientras los demás dormían. Mal Keshar, por supuesto, "
"se aseguraba de mantenernos despiertos durante cada turno contando historias "
"de sus hazañas pasadas; para nuestra desgracia, la mayoría de ellas "
"implicaba la muerte de personas inocentes —y a veces no tan inocentes— "
"descritas con vívido detalle.\n"
"\n"
"Continuamos usando la misma estrategia cada noche en adelante, con Elynia "
"relevando a Mal Keshar en ocasiones para entretener a nuestros compañeros "
"vivos con anécdotas menos macabras. Presumía de que no necesitaba dormir tan "
"seguido ni por tanto tiempo como la mayoría de nosotros, la gente normal, "
"pero, como llegué a comprobar, eso simplemente no era cierto."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:448
msgid ""
"It was at the end of one of my shifts. I went to Elynia’s tent to wake her "
"up for hers, but this time I did not find her up and ready to take her "
"place; she had clearly made the attempt and somehow tumbled back into bed "
"instead.\n"
"\n"
"I opted to let her sleep and went back to keeping guard with Mal Keshar by "
"my side, doing my best effort to ignore his teasing until dawn broke. And "
"then, I had to endure Elynia scolding me for breaking protocol."
msgstr ""
"Fue al final de uno de mis turnos. Fui a la tienda de Elynia para "
"despertarla y que tomara el suyo, pero esta vez no la encontré despierta y "
"lista para ocupar su puesto; claramente lo había intentado y de algún modo "
"había terminado de nuevo en la cama.\n"
"\n"
"Opté por dejarla dormir y volví a vigilar con Mal Keshar a mi lado, haciendo "
"mi mayor esfuerzo por ignorar sus burlas hasta que amaneció. Y entonces, "
"tuve que soportar a Elynia regañándome por romper el protocolo."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]: type=Walking Corpse,Soulless, type=Walking Corpse,Soulless
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:453
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/18_Ashes_of_Wesmere.cfg:4
msgid "Ashes of Wesmere"
msgstr "Cenizas de Wesmere"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:454
msgid ""
"Six more days passed before we reached the end of the mountains, and we came "
"upon the desolate landscape that once saw three godlike beings do battle for "
"Irdya’s fate."
msgstr ""
"Pasaron seis días más antes de que llegáramos al final de las montañas, y "
"nos topamos con el paisaje desolado que en otro tiempo fue escenario de la "
"batalla de tres seres casi divinos por el destino de Irdya."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:463
msgid ""
"I have never been the kind of elf who would sit in a tree’s shade, reflect "
"on the trials and tribulations of life, and record those profound thoughts "
"onto paper. However, Anlindë always thought that others could benefit from "
"reading a personal chronicle of our journey across the continent, especially "
"if something were to happen to me on the field.\n"
"\n"
"In hindsight, I may have been far too reckless and brash in battle, putting "
"my life in danger too often without any consideration for my friends and "
"subjects. For that I wish to apologize to whomever may read this, in case I "
"never have the chance to do so in the flesh."
msgstr ""
"Nunca he sido el tipo de elfo que se sienta a la sombra de un árbol a "
"reflexionar sobre las pruebas y tribulaciones de la vida, o que registre "
"pensamientos profundos en el papel. Sin embargo, Anlindë siempre pensó que "
"otros podrían beneficiarse al leer una crónica personal de nuestro viaje por "
"el continente, especialmente si algo llegara a sucederme en el campo de "
"batalla.\n"
"\n"
"En retrospectiva, tal vez fui demasiado imprudente y temerario en combate, "
"poniendo mi vida en peligro con demasiada frecuencia sin considerar a mis "
"amigos y súbditos. Por eso deseo disculparme ante quien pueda leer esto, en "
"caso de que nunca tenga la oportunidad de hacerlo en persona."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]: type=Verlissh Matrix Core
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:468
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/19_Under_the_Sands.cfg:4
msgid "Under the Sands"
msgstr "Bajo las arenas"

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:468
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/19x_Crossroads.cfg:4
msgid "Crossroads"
msgstr "Encrucijada"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:469
msgid ""
"I do not know for certain whether I would have changed our fate had I the "
"power. There was a lesson to be learned from our next encounter with the "
"enemy, and perhaps, in time, it would prove crucial for our survival.\n"
"\n"
"Because soon after entering the caverns we would begin to realize the full "
"breadth of the menace that threatened to end all life on Irdya, and I would "
"personally bear witness to the terrifying power of Chaos."
msgstr ""
"No sé con certeza si habría cambiado nuestro destino de haber tenido el "
"poder. Había una lección que aprender de nuestro próximo encuentro con el "
"enemigo y, quizá, con el tiempo resultaría crucial para nuestra "
"supervivencia.\n"
"\n"
"Porque poco después de entrar en las cavernas comenzaríamos a comprender la "
"magnitud de la amenaza que pretendía acabar con toda la vida en Irdya, y yo "
"sería testigo directo del aterrador poder del Caos."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:480
msgid ""
"The devastated landscapes of the lands of Chaos were easily the best weapon "
"at the Empire’s disposal. Not only did they offer very little in the way of "
"shelter, water and food, but they were also plagued with all manner of "
"hostile creatures residing in artificial hives under the ground; the desert "
"surrounding our long lost home was a sandy paradise compared to this "
"nightmarish unknown. Bearing this in mind, perhaps the existence of a whole "
"culture dedicated to the conquest and destruction of other peoples under the "
"orders of a bellicose goddess was not as implausible as it first seemed.\n"
"\n"
"Exactly how they managed to sustain themselves on a day-to-day basis was an "
"entirely different mystery, though."
msgstr ""
"Los paisajes devastados de las tierras del Caos eran, sin duda, el mejor "
"arma a disposición del Imperio. No solo ofrecían muy poco en términos de "
"refugio, agua y alimento, sino que además estaban plagados de toda clase de "
"criaturas hostiles que habitaban en colmenas artificiales bajo tierra; el "
"desierto que rodeaba nuestro hogar perdido hacía tiempo era un paraíso de "
"arena en comparación con este desconocido y pesadillesco lugar. Teniendo "
"esto en cuenta, quizá la existencia de toda una cultura dedicada a la "
"conquista y destrucción de otros pueblos bajo las órdenes de una diosa "
"belicosa no era tan inverosímil como parecía al principio.\n"
"\n"
"Sin embargo, cómo lograban mantenerse día a día era un misterio totalmente "
"distinto."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:485
msgid ""
"I tried my best to keep my mind clear at night, but the memories of my last "
"encounter with the Emperor continued to haunt me during my sleep. That "
"vision of twisted metal and flesh, those ominous glowing eyes... his "
"metallic voice booming and echoing in the darkness of a cavern, overlapping "
"the constant noise of machines and creatures I had never heard before. Next "
"to him stood somebody else, the silhouette of a woman holding a book of some "
"sort.\n"
"\n"
"“She sees you as little more than a burden she constantly has to watch and "
"protect while she and the necromancer do all the actual fighting.”\n"
"\n"
"“She knew that Anlindë’s sacrifice would hardly serve any purpose at all. "
"She let her go, and you did nothing to prevent that tragedy.”"
msgstr ""
"Hice lo posible por mantener la mente despejada por las noches, pero los "
"recuerdos de mi último encuentro con el Emperador seguían atormentándome en "
"sueños. Aquella visión de metal y carne retorcidos, esos ojos ominosos que "
"resplandecían... su voz metálica retumbando y resonando en la oscuridad de "
"una caverna, mezclándose con el ruido constante de máquinas y criaturas que "
"jamás había oído antes. A su lado había alguien más, la silueta de una mujer "
"sosteniendo algún tipo de libro.\n"
"\n"
"«Ella te ve como poco más que una carga a la que debe vigilar y proteger "
"constantemente mientras ella y el nigromante hacen toda la verdadera "
"lucha.»\n"
"\n"
"«Ella sabía que el sacrificio de Anlindë difícilmente serviría de algo. La "
"dejó ir, y tú no hiciste nada para evitar aquella tragedia.»"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:492
msgid ""
"“I am not any more responsible for your mentor’s death than the Lady of "
"Light whom you swore to protect, yet you came to my lands seeking "
"vengeance.”\n"
"\n"
"“Do you not see that she is within your reach right now?”\n"
"\n"
"“You know what you must do.”"
msgstr ""
"«No soy más responsable de la muerte de tu mentora que la Dama de la Luz a "
"quien juraste proteger, y aun así viniste a mis tierras en busca de "
"venganza.»\n"
"\n"
"«¿No ves que está a tu alcance en este mismo momento?»\n"
"\n"
"«Sabes lo que debes hacer.»"

#. [part]
#. The quoted line is also used in scenario 19.
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:500
msgid ""
"Then a voice, an alluring voice belonging, perhaps, to the woman. She spoke "
"in a language I could not understand. I focused on averting my mind from the "
"scene just as I felt my arms begin to move on their own.\n"
"\n"
"“On the surface or under the ground, it makes no difference to me, Galas. "
"The lands of Chaos are <b>my</b> domain, bestowed upon me by the Guardian of "
"Life herself. Either pledge allegiance to her, or you shall be purged as the "
"<b>intruder</b> you are!”\n"
"\n"
"Then, a sudden flash of red, followed by complete darkness."
msgstr ""
"Entonces una voz, una voz seductora que tal vez pertenecía a la mujer. Habló "
"en un idioma que no pude comprender. Me concentré en apartar mi mente de la "
"escena justo cuando sentí que mis brazos empezaban a moverse por sí solos.\n"
"\n"
"«En la superficie o bajo tierra, no hay diferencia para mí, Galas. Las "
"tierras del Caos son <b>mi</b> dominio, otorgado por la mismísima Guardiana "
"de la Vida. ¡O juras lealtad a ella, o serás purgado como el <b>intruso</b> "
"que eres!»\n"
"\n"
"Luego, un súbito destello rojo, seguido de una oscuridad completa."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:507
msgid ""
"Since that incident, the Emperor must have stopped trying to reach me and "
"take control of my body for some reason. Perhaps even with his rumored "
"power, it was not a tactic that he could use too often. Or maybe Elynia’s "
"power proved too large a hurdle to overcome now that she made sure to "
"constantly stick by my side.\n"
"\n"
"Then again, with us marching straight towards the heart of his domain there "
"was little reason to keep wasting energy when he could just patiently sit "
"and wait for his prey to come.\n"
"\n"
"I was absorbed in those thoughts one morning, when we were distracted by an "
"unexpected encounter. Up to that point, we had never suspected we were not "
"the only band of travelers on a mission in these lands."
msgstr ""
"Desde aquel incidente, el Emperador debió dejar de intentar alcanzarme y "
"controlar mi cuerpo por alguna razón. Tal vez, incluso con su poder tan "
"rumoreado, no era una táctica que pudiera usar con demasiada frecuencia. O "
"quizás el poder de Elynia resultó ser un obstáculo demasiado grande ahora "
"que se aseguraba de permanecer siempre a mi lado.\n"
"\n"
"Sin embargo, al marchar directamente hacia el corazón de su dominio, tenía "
"pocas razones para seguir gastando energía cuando podía simplemente esperar "
"pacientemente a que su presa llegara.\n"
"\n"
"Estaba absorto en esos pensamientos una mañana, cuando nos vimos "
"interrumpidos por un encuentro inesperado. Hasta ese momento, nunca habíamos "
"sospechado que no éramos el único grupo de viajeros en una misión en estas "
"tierras."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:520
msgid ""
"Thus the battle preparations began.\n"
"\n"
"Many times throughout this endless journey, I had hesitated to continue for "
"fear of putting our people’s survival at risk. But now that they were in the "
"safety of the Far North and under the command of more capable leaders than "
"I, my only fear was having my body be puppeteered by our enemies again and "
"becoming the instrument of my friends’ demise. Elynia reassured me that she "
"would not let that happen as long as she could draw breath."
msgstr ""
"Así comenzaron los preparativos para la batalla.\n"
"\n"
"Muchas veces durante este viaje interminable dudé en continuar por miedo a "
"poner en riesgo la supervivencia de nuestro pueblo. Pero ahora que estaban a "
"salvo en el Lejano Norte y bajo el mando de líderes más capaces que yo, mi "
"único temor era que mi cuerpo volviera a ser manipulado por nuestros "
"enemigos y me convirtiera en el instrumento de la perdición de mis amigos. "
"Elynia me aseguró que no permitiría que eso ocurriera mientras pudiera "
"respirar."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:525
msgid ""
"“What if you could not prevent it, though?”, I asked. “What if the unholy "
"power the Emperor wields surpasses even your own and it becomes impossible "
"to stop me?”\n"
"\n"
"She could not offer a concrete answer to the question, but I thought I could "
"read the solution in her eyes; and, as Lord Galas of the elves, I would have "
"certainly agreed that it was a reasonable course of action. Now I was no "
"longer sure. I remembered the dwarves’ stories of our desert kin, and "
"wondered if my own story would soon reach as bitter an end as it did for "
"many of Kalehssar’s allies."
msgstr ""
"«¿Y si no pudieras evitarlo?», pregunté. «¿Y si el poder impío que empuña el "
"Emperador supera incluso el tuyo y resulta imposible detenerme?»\n"
"\n"
"No pudo darme una respuesta concreta, pero creí leer la solución en sus "
"ojos; y, como Señor Galas de los elfos, sin duda habría considerado que era "
"un curso de acción razonable. Ahora ya no estaba tan seguro. Recordé las "
"historias de los enanos sobre nuestros parientes del desierto y me pregunté "
"si mi propia historia pronto tendría un final tan amargo como el de muchos "
"aliados de Kalehssar."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:530
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/20_The_Heart.cfg:4
msgid "The Heart"
msgstr "El corazón"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:531
msgid ""
"Then I decided I would not go down without a fight. This so-called Emperor "
"would feel my wrath. He would pay dearly for what he did to Anlindë, to my "
"lord Lédinor, and to the thousands of elves he tortured and slaughtered in "
"our Valley.\n"
"\n"
"I would make sure to bring an end to his reign of blood and destruction, or "
"perish in the attempt."
msgstr ""
"Entonces decidí que no caería sin luchar. Ese supuesto Emperador sentiría mi "
"ira. Pagaría caro por lo que le hizo a Anlindë, a mi señor Lédinor y a los "
"miles de elfos que torturó y masacró en nuestro Valle.\n"
"\n"
"Me aseguraría de poner fin a su reinado de sangre y destrucción, o perecería "
"en el intento."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:542
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/21_Innuendo.cfg:4
msgid "Innuendo"
msgstr "Insinuación"

#. [part]
#. [scenario]: type=Door
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:551
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/22A_Face_of_the_Enemy.cfg:4
msgid "Face of the Enemy"
msgstr "El Rostro del Enemigo"

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:560
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/22B_Dark_Hive.cfg:4
msgid "The Dark Hive"
msgstr "La Colmena Oscura"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:569
msgid ""
"“There are things more important in this world than the lives of the few, "
"and things worse than the death of the many.”\n"
"\n"
"No matter how hard I tried to make sense of Elynia’s words, I could not see "
"how they justified letting the demoness go. To take pity on her because of "
"her condition seemed reckless and unnecessary. So what if she was only "
"following orders? She certainly did not seem lacking of her own will."
msgstr ""
"«Hay cosas más importantes en este mundo que la vida de unos pocos, y cosas "
"peores que la muerte de muchos.»\n"
"\n"
"Por más que intenté darle sentido a las palabras de Elynia, no pude ver cómo "
"justificaban dejar ir a la demonio. Tenerle piedad por su condición parecía "
"imprudente e innecesario. ¿Y qué si solo seguía órdenes? Ciertamente no "
"parecía carecer de voluntad propia."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]: type=Cockatrice}
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:574
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/23A_Into_the_Lair.cfg:4
msgid "Into the Lair"
msgstr "En la guarida"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:575
msgid ""
"There certainly has been something amiss about Elynia, and even Mal Keshar, "
"ever since we set foot in enemy territory; walking into the Heart fortress "
"only appeared to make things worse. Then again, I did not exactly feel like "
"myself either. I began to fear that the very atmosphere of this place was "
"seeping into our heads and clouding our thoughts and that things would "
"spiral out of control before we could achieve our objective."
msgstr ""
"Sin duda había algo extraño en Elynia, e incluso en Mal Keshar, desde que "
"pusimos un pie en territorio enemigo; adentrarnos en la fortaleza del "
"Corazón solo parecía empeorar las cosas. Por otra parte, yo tampoco me "
"sentía exactamente como yo mismo. Empecé a temer que la propia atmósfera de "
"este lugar se estaba filtrando en nuestras mentes y nublando nuestros "
"pensamientos, y que todo se saldría de control antes de que pudiéramos "
"cumplir nuestro objetivo."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:584
msgid ""
"An uneasy silence arose. The Chaos Emperor lay amongst the carnage, his "
"mechanical body broken and singed, seeping rivulets of blood that streaked "
"across the patterned floor. And Elynia... it was as if Argan’s death had "
"shattered something inside her. She wailed, dragging her hands across the "
"crimson floor as if she could gather her lover’s lifeblood in her hands.\n"
"\n"
"I realized, then, that my presence was pointless; there was nothing I could "
"do to ease her pain. She had held herself together this long by sheer force "
"of will; now, that will was spent. I tightened my grip on my sword as she "
"buried her face in her hands and wept, heedless of the smears of red they "
"left behind. In all this time, I had thought I knew loss — Anlindë, who was "
"like a mother to me, scores of my friends and kinsmen — but in truth, I did "
"not. I did not know the weight of centuries she bore upon her shoulders, nor "
"the heartbreak of dashed hopes and broken promises that now lay prone at her "
"feet.\n"
"\n"
"In truth, I could never aspire to become as strong of soul as she. She had "
"foreseen this conclusion long before any of us, yet continued onwards. Would "
"I have had the courage to do the same, were I faced with the same choice — "
"strike down someone whom I loved, or die and let the world suffer for my "
"selfishness?"
msgstr ""
"Se alzó un silencio incómodo. El Emperador del Caos yacía entre la "
"carnicería, su cuerpo mecánico roto y chamuscado, exudando hilos de sangre "
"que se deslizaban por el suelo decorado. Y Elynia... era como si la muerte "
"de Argan hubiera destrozado algo en su interior. Ella gemía, arrastrando las "
"manos sobre el piso carmesí como si pudiera recoger la sangre vital de su "
"amado en sus manos.\n"
"\n"
"Me di cuenta entonces de que mi presencia era inútil; no había nada que "
"pudiera hacer para aliviar su dolor. Se había mantenido firme todo este "
"tiempo por pura fuerza de voluntad; ahora, esa voluntad estaba agotada. "
"Apreté el puño sobre mi espada mientras ella enterraba el rostro entre sus "
"manos y lloraba, sin importarle las manchas rojas que dejaban atrás. Durante "
"todo este tiempo creí conocer la pérdida — Anlindë, que fue como una madre "
"para mí, decenas de amigos y parientes — pero en verdad no era así. No "
"conocía el peso de los siglos que ella cargaba sobre sus hombros, ni el "
"desgarrador dolor de las esperanzas frustradas y las promesas rotas que "
"ahora yacían a sus pies.\n"
"\n"
"En realidad, jamás podría aspirar a tener un espíritu tan fuerte como el de "
"ella. Había previsto este desenlace mucho antes que cualquiera de nosotros, "
"y aun así continuó adelante. ¿Habría tenido yo el valor de hacer lo mismo, "
"de enfrentar la misma elección: abatir a alguien a quien amaba, o morir y "
"dejar que el mundo sufriera por mi egoísmo?"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:591
msgid ""
"I felt a sudden urge to embrace and comfort her, but I did not; I could not "
"intrude upon her grief with my own foolish feelings.\n"
"\n"
"Instead, I turned to Mal Keshar, and tried to see through his perpetually "
"expressionless face. I had never given much thought to his story or his "
"life. It may have been a silly thought, but for a brief moment I wondered if "
"he had ever felt this loss himself. The way he uttered those words to Elynia "
"seemed to suggest that he had at least researched the subject of "
"resurrection in the past. For power, or to bring back a loved one? I doubt I "
"will ever gather the courage to ask."
msgstr ""
"Sentí un repentino impulso de abrazarla y consolarla, pero no lo hice; no "
"podía entrometerme en su dolor con mis propios y necios sentimientos.\n"
"\n"
"En cambio, me volví hacia Mal Keshar e intenté ver a través de su rostro "
"perpetuamente inexpresivo. Nunca había pensado mucho en su historia o en su "
"vida. Tal vez fuera un pensamiento tonto, pero por un breve momento me "
"pregunté si alguna vez él mismo habría sentido esa pérdida. La forma en que "
"pronunció aquellas palabras a Elynia parecía sugerir que, al menos, había "
"investigado el tema de la resurrección en el pasado. ¿Por poder, o para "
"traer de vuelta a un ser querido? Dudo que alguna vez reúna el valor para "
"preguntarle."

#. [part]
#. [scenario]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:601
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/24_Epilogue.cfg:4
msgid "Epilogue"
msgstr "Epílogo"

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:607
msgid ""
"In the end, the entire valley where once stood the mighty capital of the "
"Chaos Empire disappeared in a matter of minutes. Even the biomechanical "
"monsters — which we once regarded as invincible foes — perished amidst the "
"destruction that erased Argan’s fortress from existence. Enemies, allies... "
"for the earth there were no colors or sides, only insignificant creatures "
"caught in its clutches as it dragged everything down to the depths of hell.\n"
"\n"
"Once nothing but an unfathomably large crater was left, the darkness of the "
"night gave way to the dawn of a new day, and Naia shone through the "
"dispersing smoke and clouds to announce the day when the ruler of Inferno "
"tasted her first defeat."
msgstr ""
"Al final, todo el valle donde una vez se erigió la poderosa capital del "
"Imperio del Caos desapareció en cuestión de minutos. Incluso los monstruos "
"biomecánicos — a los que en su día consideramos enemigos invencibles — "
"perecieron entre la destrucción que borró la fortaleza de Argan de la "
"existencia. Enemigos, aliados... para la tierra no había colores ni bandos, "
"solo criaturas insignificantes atrapadas en sus garras mientras arrastraba "
"todo hacia las profundidades del infierno.\n"
"\n"
"Cuando no quedó más que un cráter inconmensurable, la oscuridad de la noche "
"dió paso al amanecer de un nuevo día, y Naia brilló a través del humo y las "
"nubes dispersas para anunciar el día en que la soberana del Infierno probó "
"su primera derrota."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:615
msgid ""
"We abandoned the creature that once was Lord Lédinor to his death, much to "
"my regret; even though Elynia assured me that there was no way to restore "
"him to his old self, much like Argan, I hoped that perhaps we could have "
"managed to restrain him while we figured out a cure with her help. Alas, it "
"would have proved impossible to keep him from delaying our escape. I can "
"only hope his death was swift enough, assuming there was anything of him "
"left within that horrifying mutated mass of flesh.\n"
"\n"
"Uria did this to him to show us, to remind us how powerless we mere mortals "
"are against beings like her, especially now without the Union of Light and "
"Darkness. Maybe if I had not witnessed Elynia’s resoluteness first, I would "
"have bent and despaired like the goddess so wanted, but no; I would not give "
"her that pleasure now, after so much."
msgstr ""
"Abandonamos a la criatura que una vez fue Lord Lédinor a su muerte, para mi "
"gran pesar; aunque Elynia me aseguró que no había forma de devolverlo a su "
"antiguo ser, al igual que Argan, esperaba que quizás hubiéramos logrado "
"retenerlo mientras buscábamos una cura con su ayuda. Por desgracia, habría "
"sido imposible evitar que retrasara nuestra huida. Solo puedo esperar que su "
"muerte haya sido lo bastante rápida, suponiendo que quedara algo de él "
"dentro de aquella horrenda masa de carne mutada.\n"
"\n"
"Uria le hizo eso para mostrarnos, para recordarnos cuán impotentes somos los "
"simples mortales ante seres como ella, especialmente ahora sin la Unión de "
"Luz y Oscuridad. Quizá si no hubiera presenciado primero la determinación de "
"Elynia, me habría doblado y desesperado como tanto deseaba la diosa, pero "
"no; no le daría ese placer ahora, después de tanto."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:622
msgid ""
"Even though Elynia assured me that there was no way to restore Lédinor to "
"his old self, much like Argan, I hoped that perhaps we could have managed to "
"restrain him while we figured out a cure with her help. Alas, it would have "
"proved impossible to keep him from delaying our escape. At least we put an "
"end to his suffering soon enough, assuming there was anything of him left "
"within that horrifying mutated mass of flesh.\n"
"\n"
"Uria did this to him to show us, to remind us how powerless we mere mortals "
"are against beings like her, especially now without the Union of Light and "
"Darkness. Maybe if I had not witnessed Elynia’s resoluteness first, I would "
"have bent and despaired like the goddess so wanted, but no; I would not give "
"her that pleasure now, after so much."
msgstr ""
"Aunque Elynia me aseguró que no había forma de devolver a Lédinor a su "
"antiguo ser, al igual que Argan, esperaba que quizás hubiéramos logrado "
"retenerlo mientras buscábamos una cura con su ayuda. Por desgracia, habría "
"sido imposible evitar que retrasara nuestra huida. Al menos pusimos fin a su "
"sufrimiento lo bastante pronto, suponiendo que quedara algo de él dentro de "
"aquella horrenda masa de carne mutada.\n"
"\n"
"Uria le hizo eso para mostrarnos, para recordarnos cuán impotentes somos los "
"simples mortales ante seres como ella, especialmente ahora sin la Unión de "
"Luz y Oscuridad. Quizá si no hubiera presenciado primero la determinación de "
"Elynia, me habría doblado y desesperado como tanto deseaba la diosa, pero "
"no; no le daría ese placer ahora, después de tanto."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:632
msgid ""
"Only us three made it out of the fortress alive, along with Igor. We tried "
"to locate the dwarves, but enemy troops arrived to inspect the ruins of the "
"Heart before we could finish our search. The evidence we found suggested "
"that our allies had to retreat for some reason, possibly while we were busy "
"battling Elyssa in the Dark Hive.\n"
"\n"
"We ran. We ran as far as we could, and then continued traveling west, "
"towards the ocean. The next few weeks went by in a hazy flash of sand and "
"mountains, while we struggled to pass unnoticed through hostile territory. "
"Fortunately, they were probably too busy mourning their Emperor’s death — if "
"they even have such a custom — to bother with hunting us down."
msgstr ""
"Solo nosotros tres logramos salir con vida de la fortaleza, junto con Igor. "
"Intentamos localizar a los enanos, pero las tropas enemigas llegaron para "
"inspeccionar las ruinas del Corazón antes de que pudiéramos terminar nuestra "
"búsqueda. Las pruebas que encontramos sugerían que nuestros aliados habían "
"tenido que retirarse por alguna razón, posiblemente mientras nosotros "
"estábamos ocupados combatiendo a Elyssa en la Colmena Oscura.\n"
"\n"
"Huidos, corrimos tan lejos como pudimos y luego continuamos viajando hacia "
"el oeste, hacia el océano. Las semanas siguientes transcurrieron como un "
"veloz torbellino de arena y montañas, mientras luchábamos por pasar "
"inadvertidos a través del territorio hostil. Por fortuna, probablemente "
"estaban demasiado ocupados llorando la muerte de su Emperador —si es que "
"siquiera tienen tal costumbre— para molestarse en cazarnos."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:639
msgid ""
"Only us three made it out of the fortress alive. We tried to locate the "
"dwarves, but enemy troops arrived to inspect the ruins of the Heart before "
"we could finish our search. The evidence we found suggested that our allies "
"had to retreat for some reason, possibly while we were busy battling Elyssa "
"in the Dark Hive.\n"
"\n"
"We ran. We ran as far as we could, and then continued traveling west, "
"towards the ocean. The next few weeks went by in a hazy flash of sand and "
"mountains, while we struggled to pass unnoticed through hostile territory. "
"Fortunately, they were probably too busy mourning their Emperor’s death — if "
"they even have such a custom — to bother with hunting us down."
msgstr ""
"Solo nosotros tres logramos salir con vida de la fortaleza. Intentamos "
"localizar a los enanos, pero las tropas enemigas llegaron para inspeccionar "
"las ruinas del Corazón antes de que pudiéramos terminar nuestra búsqueda. "
"Las pruebas que encontramos sugerían que nuestros aliados habían tenido que "
"retirarse por alguna razón, posiblemente mientras nosotros estábamos "
"ocupados combatiendo a Elyssa en la Colmena Oscura.\n"
"\n"
"Huidos, corrimos tan lejos como pudimos y luego continuamos viajando hacia "
"el oeste, hacia el océano. Las semanas siguientes transcurrieron como un "
"veloz torbellino de arena y montañas, mientras luchábamos por pasar "
"inadvertidos a través del territorio hostil. Por fortuna, probablemente "
"estaban demasiado ocupados llorando la muerte de su Emperador —si es que "
"siquiera tienen tal costumbre— para molestarse en cazarnos."

#. [part]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/storytxt.cfg:646
msgid ""
"The storm that drove us out of hiding is over now, but our journey has only "
"just begun. Darker days are coming, and it will take our best effort to put "
"an end to this war now that Uria has taken notice of our existence. Even now "
"I worry for the safety of my kin up in the Far North.\n"
"\n"
"But as long as we stick together, I feel that we may yet have a chance "
"against the evil force that threatens to take Irdya from us.”"
msgstr ""
"La tormenta que nos obligó a salir de nuestro escondite ha terminado ahora, "
"pero nuestro viaje apenas comienza. Se avecinan días más oscuros, y "
"requerirá nuestro mayor esfuerzo para poner fin a esta guerra ahora que Uria "
"ha tomado nota de nuestra existencia. Incluso ahora me preocupa la seguridad "
"de los míos en el Lejano Norte.\n"
"\n"
"Pero mientras nos mantengamos unidos, siento que aún podemos tener una "
"oportunidad contra la fuerza maligna que amenaza con arrebatarnos Irdya.»"

#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/taint-utils.cfg:6
msgid "Undead units (except Liches) are subject to taint in this scenario"
msgstr ""
"Las unidades no muertas (excepto Liches) están sujetas a corrupción en este "
"escenario"

#. [set_menu_item]: id=wmi_taint_help
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/taint-utils.cfg:70
msgid "About Taint"
msgstr "Acerca de la corrupción"

#. [event]: id=taint:help
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/macros/taint-utils.cfg:166
msgid ""
"Undead units — except Liches — that spend a turn more than six tiles away "
"from Mal Keshar or Elynia will be afflicted with a stackable <b>taint</b> "
"effect, which weakens their attack damage and hitpoints by 10%. Once the "
"effect reaches its <b>fourth</b> level, you will permanently and "
"irreversibly lose control of the unit!\n"
"\n"
"To remove the taint effect, move the unit back into range, which will clear "
"one level of the effect each turn. Undead units which start their turn "
"adjacent to Mal Keshar or Elynia, gain a level, or attain an AMLA upgrade "
"will have the taint effect fully cleared instantly."
msgstr ""
"Las unidades no muertas —excepto Liches— que pasen un turno a más de seis "
"casillas de Mal Keshar o Elynia quedarán afectadas por un efecto acumulable "
"de <b>corrupción</b>, que debilita su daño de ataque y sus puntos de vida en "
"un 10 %. ¡Cuando el efecto alcance su <b>cuarto</b> nivel, perderás el "
"control de la unidad de forma permanente e irreversible!\n"
"\n"
"Para eliminar el efecto de corrupción, regresa la unidad al rango, lo que "
"eliminará un nivel del efecto por turno. Las unidades no muertas que "
"comiencen su turno adyacentes a Mal Keshar o Elynia, suban de nivel o "
"consigan una mejora AMLA tendrán el efecto de corrupción eliminado por "
"completo de inmediato."

