#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/15_Shadows_of_Time.cfg:111
msgid "team_name^Undead"
msgstr "Nomuertos"

#. [side]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:113
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/05b_Cursed_Plateau.cfg:150
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/07_Goliath.cfg:84
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/08_Errand_of_Hope.cfg:173
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/09_The_Library.cfg:150
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/10_The_Source_of_Light.cfg:112
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/10_The_Source_of_Light.cfg:166
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/10_The_Source_of_Light.cfg:201
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/10_The_Source_of_Light.cfg:237
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/10_The_Source_of_Light.cfg:279
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/12_The_Escape.cfg:115
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/22A_Face_of_the_Enemy.cfg:160
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/22B_Dark_Hive.cfg:162
msgid "team_name^Cave Creatures"
msgstr "Criaturas de las cavernas"

#. [event]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:180
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/10_The_Source_of_Light.cfg:506
msgid "Explore the caves"
msgstr "Explore las cavernas"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:196
msgid ""
"We lost our home... many of our children and elders... and our lord, at the "
"hands of those fiends... What will we do now? Where will we go?"
msgstr ""
"Hemos perdido nuestro hogar... a muchos de nuestros niños y ancianos... y a "
"nuestro señor, a manos de esos demonios... ¿Qué haremos ahora? ¿Adónde "
"iremos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:201
msgid ""
"Don’t despair, Galas. This is not the first time our civilization has been "
"through trials like this. Invaders may defile our lands, the suns may burn "
"our forests to the ground, but as long as we stand we may be yet able to "
"find a new place to call home."
msgstr ""
"No desesperes, Galas. No es la primera vez que nuestra civilización pasa por "
"pruebas como esta. Los invasores pueden profanar nuestras tierras, los soles "
"pueden quemar nuestros bosques hasta convertirlos en cenizas, pero mientras "
"sigamos en pie aún podremos encontrar un nuevo lugar al que llamar hogar."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:206
msgid ""
"I profoundly hope so... Anlindë, you mentioned something about an evil force "
"before counseling flight. What did you mean?"
msgstr ""
"Lo espero profundamente... Anlindë, mencionaste algo sobre una fuerza "
"maligna antes de aconsejar huir. ¿A qué te referías?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:211
msgid ""
"There is some great evil aiding those humans. Not merely ordinary "
"necromancers and war-beasts, but something worse... something I believed had "
"been vanquished by our civilization before. I need to ponder this further. "
"Now, I suggest we proceed as swiftly as we may. Our valley..."
msgstr ""
"Hay un gran mal que está ayudando a esos humanos. No se trata solo de "
"nigromantes ordinarios y bestias de guerra, sino de algo peor... algo que "
"creía que nuestra civilización ya había vencido antes. Necesito reflexionar "
"más sobre ello. Ahora sugiero que avancemos tan rápido como podamos. Nuestro "
"valle..."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:216
msgid "I would prefer to not think about it."
msgstr "Preferiría no pensar en ello."

#. [message]: role=supporter
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:221
msgid ""
"Would that we had more experience at moving in this darkness. This will be a "
"long march."
msgstr ""
"Ojalá tuviéramos más experiencia moviéndonos en esta oscuridad. Será una "
"larga marcha."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:245
msgid "Undead! There are undead here!"
msgstr "¡No-muertos! ¡Hay no-muertos aquí!"

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:250
msgid ""
"They must have settled in here only recently, or they would have surely "
"announced their presence in our valley before."
msgstr ""
"Seguramente se establecieron aquí hace poco, o de lo contrario ya habrían "
"anunciado su presencia en nuestro valle."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:255
msgid ""
"If we press forward, we may be able to find and strike their master down. "
"Not that we have much of a choice now, with everyone trapped underground."
msgstr ""
"Si avanzamos, puede que logremos encontrar y derrotar a su maestro. No es "
"que tengamos muchas opciones ahora, con todos atrapados bajo tierra."

#. [event]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:270
msgid "Find the source of the roaming undead"
msgstr "Encuentra la fuente de los no-muertos errantes"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:299
msgid "Who is this foul enemy that seeks our death?"
msgstr "¿Quién es este vil enemigo que busca nuestra muerte?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:304
msgid ""
"Have you elves not realized the folly of trifling with the forces that lay "
"in the darkest depths of Irdya? I am Mal Keshar, and these caverns belong to "
"me now. Leave at once or meet your doom!"
msgstr ""
"¿Acaso no se han dado cuenta, elfos, de la locura que es jugar con las "
"fuerzas que yacen en las profundidades más oscuras de Irdya? Soy Mal Keshar, "
"y estas cavernas me pertenecen ahora. ¡Váyanse de inmediato o encuentren su "
"perdición!"

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:309
msgid "Mal Keshar? That name..."
msgstr "¿Mal Keshar? Ese nombre..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:314
msgid "I said, <b>leave</b>!"
msgstr "¡He dicho que se <b>vayan</b>!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:319
msgid ""
"Listen, necromancer. We seek no quarrel with you. We have lost our home to "
"foes of a power possibly greater than yours. Returning is not an option. If "
"you want us gone, you will have to allow us passage through these caves."
msgstr ""
"Escucha, nigromante. No buscamos pelea contigo. Hemos perdido nuestro hogar "
"a manos de enemigos de un poder posiblemente mayor que el tuyo. Volver no es "
"una opción. Si quieres que nos vayamos, tendrás que permitirnos el paso por "
"estas cavernas."

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:324
msgid "Galas, you are not expecting that to work, are you—"
msgstr "Galas, no esperarás que eso funcione, ¿verdad?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:329
msgid ""
"Ha, ha, ha, ha! Greater than mine, you say? My, you are but a young little "
"elf of the forests! I had thought your kind’s existence had ended for good "
"after the Golden Age! I am truly amazed! Let us put an end to your aimless "
"wandering, then. At least you shall perish at the hands of a figure of "
"legend rather than savage orcs or humans of the sands!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ja, ja, ja, ja! ¿Más grande que el mío, dices? Vaya, ¡eres apenas un joven "
"elfo de los bosques! Pensé que la existencia de tu raza había terminado para "
"siempre tras la Edad Dorada. ¡Estoy verdaderamente sorprendido! Pongamos fin "
"a su deambular sin rumbo, entonces. Al menos perecerán a manos de una figura "
"legendaria, y no de orcos salvajes o humanos de las arenas."

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:334
msgid "His banter is truly obnoxious."
msgstr "Su parloteo es verdaderamente insoportable."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:339
msgid "Anlindë, do you think we may be able to destroy this lich?"
msgstr "Anlindë, ¿crees que podremos destruir a este liche?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:344
msgid ""
"Incapacitate, perhaps; but if it’s the same lich I am thinking of, it might "
"not be within our power to banish him permanently from the physical realm."
msgstr ""
"Incapacitarlo, tal vez; pero si es el mismo liche en el que estoy pensando, "
"puede que no esté en nuestro poder desterrarlo permanentemente del plano "
"físico."

#. [event]
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:354
msgid "Defeat Mal Keshar"
msgstr "Derrota a Mal Keshar"

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:392
msgid ""
"I have not employed this kind of magic in a lifetime, but as our young "
"leader said, we do not have much of a choice now."
msgstr ""
"No he empleado este tipo de magia en toda una vida, pero como dijo nuestro "
"joven líder, ahora no tenemos muchas opciones."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:408
msgid "What— what is this curse?"
msgstr "¿Q-qué es esta maldición?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:422
msgid "I cannot... believe it..."
msgstr "No puedo... creerlo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. The elf in question is Anlindë.
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:464
msgid ""
"How can it be? I have been defeated... my long battle against the orcs is "
"lost! What are you waiting for, elf?"
msgstr ""
"¿Cómo puede ser? He sido derrotado... ¡mi larga batalla contra los orcos se "
"ha perdido! ¿Qué esperas, elfa?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:469
msgid ""
"You are a relic from an era long gone, Mal Keshar, or should I say... Malin "
"Keshar? The one who fell to the darkness fighting a noble cause with tainted "
"means. Your life story has served as a cautionary tale for an eternity, and "
"you are now the unliving proof that the glories of the Golden Age are dead. "
"Yes, destroying you would rid this ruined land of a threat that pales in "
"comparison to what roams above the surface as we speak..."
msgstr ""
"Eres una reliquia de una era ya extinta, Mal Keshar, o debería decir... "
"¿Malin Keshar? El que cayó en la oscuridad luchando por una causa noble con "
"medios corruptos. Tu historia de vida ha servido como advertencia durante "
"toda una eternidad, y ahora eres la prueba no viviente de que las glorias de "
"la Edad Dorada están muertas. Sí, destruirte libraría a esta tierra "
"arruinada de una amenaza que palidece en comparación con lo que vaga por la "
"superficie mientras hablamos..."

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:478
msgid ""
"... Although I have to admit that the notion of allowing those fiends to "
"fight you is more than a little amusing. It’s a pity that your existence is "
"a crime... against nature... that we cannot let go unpunished."
msgstr ""
"... Aunque debo admitir que la idea de permitir que esos demonios luchen "
"contigo es más que un poco divertida. Es una lástima que tu existencia sea "
"un crimen... contra la naturaleza... que no podemos dejar sin castigo."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:483
msgid ""
"I sense hesitation in your words. Why is that? Does your kind still remember "
"what Wesnoth did to us all?"
msgstr ""
"Siento dudas en tus palabras. ¿Por qué? ¿Acaso tu raza aún recuerda lo que "
"Wesnoth nos hizo a todos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:488
msgid "Wesnoth?"
msgstr "¿Wesnoth?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:493
msgid "The name of an empire long dead. It’s not important."
msgstr "El nombre de un imperio muerto hace mucho. No es importante."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:498
msgid ""
"Are you not curious about what has transpired in the expanse it once "
"covered? You came to me fleeing a mighty foe; did it come from those lands? "
"South of the Swamps of Dread, and west of the Silver Lands?"
msgstr ""
"¿No sienten curiosidad por lo que ha sucedido en la extensión que alguna vez "
"cubrió? Vinieron a mí huyendo de un enemigo poderoso; ¿acaso proviene de "
"esas tierras? ¿Al sur de los Pantanos del Pavor y al oeste de las Tierras "
"Plateadas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:503
msgid "That is not important—"
msgstr "Eso no es importante—"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:508
msgid ""
"I know many things. I know your kind always punished necromancers for "
"disturbing the dead. You thought us the foulest evil imaginable, but you "
"were wrong. I have seen and learned of things that even I would consider "
"abominable. For all this eternity after the Fall, I have been haunting the "
"sands by night, slaughtering orcs in their sleep and hoarding every piece of "
"information I can gather about the new empire that has arisen amidst the "
"debris of the past epoch."
msgstr ""
"Sé muchas cosas. Sé que tu raza siempre castigó a los nigromantes por "
"perturbar a los muertos. Nos consideraban el mal más vil imaginable, pero "
"estaban equivocados. He visto y aprendido cosas que incluso yo consideraría "
"abominables. Durante toda esta eternidad tras la Caída, he rondado las "
"arenas de noche, masacrando orcos en su sueño y acumulando cada fragmento de "
"información que puedo reunir sobre el nuevo imperio que ha surgido entre los "
"escombros de la era pasada."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:513
msgid ""
"Alas, you have waited long enough to end this and it’s rather unmannerly of "
"me to keep interrupting you. Go ahead, finish me once and for all!"
msgstr ""
"Pero basta, ya han esperado demasiado para acabar con esto, y es bastante "
"descortés de mi parte seguir interrumpiéndolos. Vamos, ¡acaben conmigo de "
"una vez por todas!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:518
msgid "No. What do you know, necromancer? Tell us."
msgstr "No. ¿Qué sabes, nigromante? Cuéntanos."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:523
msgid ""
"It was a few centuries ago... A malign shadow emanating from the Vast Ocean "
"covered the lands, and an evil presence infected every living creature. "
"Humans from the coastal regions began raiding and destroying what human, "
"elvish, and orcish settlements they could find that would not join them in "
"alliance. In time, they would bring new allies from beyond this world — "
"demons. Your people still remember them, don’t you?"
msgstr ""
"Fue hace unos cuantos siglos... Una sombra maligna emanando del Gran Océano "
"cubrió las tierras, y una presencia malvada infectó a toda criatura "
"viviente. Los humanos de las regiones costeras comenzaron a saquear y "
"destruir cualquier asentamiento humano, élfico u orco que no se uniera a "
"ellos en alianza. Con el tiempo, trajeron nuevos aliados de más allá de este "
"mundo: demonios. Tu gente todavía los recuerda, ¿verdad?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:528
msgid ""
"We... our sages do, but... How can this be possible? The Demon Lord was "
"vanquished by the Lady of Light long ago!"
msgstr ""
"Nosotros... nuestros sabios sí, pero... ¿Cómo es esto posible? ¡El Señor de "
"los Demonios fue derrotado por la Dama de la Luz hace mucho tiempo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:533
msgid "Lady of Light?"
msgstr "¿Dama de la Luz?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:538
msgid ""
"Ah, but that was a mere foretaste of our doom. Something or someone "
"apparently opened a portal — a new one — to the very heart of Inferno, "
"unleashing the forces of evil and allowing them to cross the barrier "
"dividing our realm from theirs. This may have been done from our world, or "
"it may not. Arrogant unscrupulous magi cast us into this chaotic future "
"before when they raised the two unnatural suns, after all. But yes... the "
"humans are building a new empire of blood and destruction, and from what I "
"gather you are the victims of its northwards expansion."
msgstr ""
"Ah, pero aquello fue solo un anticipo de nuestra perdición. Algo o alguien "
"abrió un portal —uno nuevo— al mismísimo corazón del Infierno, liberando las "
"fuerzas del mal y permitiéndoles cruzar la barrera que separa nuestro reino "
"del suyo. Esto pudo haberse hecho desde nuestro mundo, o tal vez no. Después "
"de todo, fueron magos arrogantes y sin escrúpulos quienes nos arrojaron a "
"este futuro caótico cuando levantaron los dos soles antinaturales. Pero "
"sí... los humanos están construyendo un nuevo imperio de sangre y "
"destrucción, y por lo que veo ustedes son las víctimas de su expansión hacia "
"el norte."

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:543
msgid ""
"Then these caves are definitely not safe anymore. We need to escape — but "
"supposing we can, for how long will we be able to avoid our enemy?"
msgstr ""
"Entonces estas cavernas definitivamente ya no son seguras. Necesitamos "
"escapar, pero suponiendo que podamos hacerlo, ¿cuánto tiempo podremos evitar "
"a nuestro enemigo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:548
msgid ""
"You would be killed, tortured, or converted by them in a matter of hours, "
"perhaps minutes, even seconds. You are few to their many, and lack the power "
"necessary to combat the demonic hordes. Not even I have <i>that</i> fabled "
"power — but I care little about it. I do not fear an end to my undeath. I "
"have nothing left; all that I once loved has been scoured away by pitiless "
"time."
msgstr ""
"Serían asesinados, torturados o convertidos por ellos en cuestión de horas, "
"quizá minutos, incluso segundos. Ustedes son pocos contra sus muchos, y "
"carecen del poder necesario para combatir a las hordas demoníacas. Ni "
"siquiera yo poseo <i>ese</i> poder legendario... pero poco me importa. No "
"temo al final de mi no-muerte. No me queda nada; todo lo que una vez amé ha "
"sido borrado por el tiempo implacable."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:553
msgid ""
"Anlindë, what is the point of fleeing from those fiends to a new and safe "
"home like cowards if they will surely find us again? For how long can we "
"delay our downfall? Why are we not fighting the enemy?"
msgstr ""
"Anlindë, ¿de qué sirve huir de esos demonios hacia un nuevo y seguro hogar "
"como cobardes, si seguramente nos encontrarán de nuevo? ¿Por cuánto tiempo "
"podremos retrasar nuestra caída? ¿Por qué no estamos luchando contra el "
"enemigo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:558
msgid ""
"Our kin tried before, Galas, and we became the witnesses to their failure. "
"We have no aid or craft that they did not."
msgstr ""
"Nuestros parientes lo intentaron antes, Galas, y fuimos testigos de su "
"fracaso. No tenemos ninguna ayuda ni habilidad que ellos no tuvieran."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:563
msgid ""
"Perhaps this will interest you: the wielders of the Union did not die after "
"that catastrophe you insist on only vaguely referencing throughout this "
"conversation. Have you all forgotten that they roamed Irdya for many "
"centuries before, even exceeding the notorious lifespan of your kind?"
msgstr ""
"Quizá esto les interese: los portadores de la Unión no murieron tras esa "
"catástrofe que insisten en mencionar solo vagamente durante esta "
"conversación. ¿Han olvidado que vagaron por Irdya durante muchos siglos, "
"incluso superando la longevidad legendaria de los de su raza?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:568
msgid "The Union?"
msgstr "¿La Unión?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:573
msgid ""
"Your elder druids and sorceresses should remember that this Lady of Light "
"did not save you from that evil unaided. What won your victory was nothing "
"else than the power of the Union, at hands of the Master of Darkness <i>and</"
"i> the Lady of Light — a human and an elven lady. And you should remember "
"that they were blessed — or cursed — with eternal life."
msgstr ""
"Sus ancianos druidas y hechiceras deberían recordar que esa Dama de la Luz "
"no los salvó de ese mal por sí sola. Lo que les dio la victoria no fue otra "
"cosa que el poder de la Unión, en manos del Maestro de la Oscuridad <i>y</i> "
"la Dama de la Luz: un humano y una dama élfica. Y deberían recordar que "
"fueron bendecidos —o malditos— con la vida eterna."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:578
msgid ""
"Some sources say they descended deep into the very heart of the world... and "
"vanished into eternal slumber. It is said that the bright presence of the "
"Lady of Light still radiates from the earth where the two figures of legend "
"now lie dormant. Some claim to have followed them before they both "
"disappeared; if my memory still serves after all this time, I would probably "
"be able to pinpoint their location if I had the chance to approach that "
"region."
msgstr ""
"Algunas fuentes dicen que descendieron hasta el mismo corazón del mundo... y "
"desaparecieron en un sueño eterno. Se dice que la brillante presencia de la "
"Dama de la Luz aún irradia desde la tierra donde esas dos figuras "
"legendarias ahora yacen dormidas. Algunos afirman haberlos seguido antes de "
"que ambos desaparecieran; si mi memoria no me falla después de tanto tiempo, "
"probablemente podría señalar su ubicación si tuviera la oportunidad de "
"acercarme a esa región."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:587
msgid "Would you be willing to lead us there?"
msgstr "¿Estarías dispuesto a guiarnos hasta allí?"

#. [message]: role=supporter
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:592
msgid ""
"What?! But my lord, he is a lich — a necromancer! We cannot have such an "
"abomination on our side!"
msgstr ""
"¿¡Qué!? Pero mi señor, ¡él es un liche, un nigromante! ¡No podemos tener a "
"semejante abominación de nuestro lado!"

#. [message]: speaker=Anlindë
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:597
msgid ""
"... Times have changed, and so have our needs and methods... If Galas thinks "
"the necromancer can help us find the power that can protect the remains of "
"our civilization..."
msgstr ""
"... Los tiempos han cambiado, y también nuestras necesidades y métodos... Si "
"Galas cree que el nigromante puede ayudarnos a encontrar el poder que "
"proteja los restos de nuestra civilización..."

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:602
msgid ""
"He, he, he, he... yes... yes! I may be able to help you, as long as you "
"abide by my conditions."
msgstr ""
"Je, je, je, je... sí... ¡sí! Puede que sea capaz de ayudarlos, siempre y "
"cuando cumplan mis condiciones."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:611
msgid "And what would those be?"
msgstr "¿Y cuáles serían esas condiciones?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:616
msgid "Protection is all I want."
msgstr "Todo lo que quiero es protección."

#. [message]: role=supporter
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:621
msgid "Some of us might oppose this. My lord, please think this through!"
msgstr ""
"Algunos de nosotros podríamos oponernos a esto. ¡Mi señor, por favor "
"piénselo bien!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:630
msgid ""
"What do you think, Galas? You have lost everything — well, mostly. I lost "
"everything too, except for my unfinished business with the orcs, and this "
"knowledge that could be placed at your service on these very simple terms. "
"It’s your decision to make, young boy."
msgstr ""
"¿Qué dices, Galas? Tú lo has perdido todo... bueno, casi todo. Yo también lo "
"he perdido todo, salvo mis asuntos pendientes con los orcos, y este "
"conocimiento que podría ponerse a tu servicio bajo estos sencillos términos. "
"La decisión es tuya, jovencito."

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: Invasion_from_the_Unknown/scenarios/03_Memories_from_the_Depths.cfg:639
msgid "I accept."
msgstr "Acepto."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
